{"id": "1378", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "The state, county, city make their own laws.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "That is what I have ran into", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "and if a person does not hire a lawyer, are not a big group, there isn't much hope for the consumer.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "The law where everyone may hire a lawyer has limits--IE: Will not take a criminal or money cases if a non profit org. or free lawyer takes the case.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "I darn sure do not understand the laws etc.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "testimony", "text": "and I have tried to read about all this for 2 years.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "testimony", "text": "Of course I'm old and 100% DAV,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "that could be it.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "303", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Debt collectors are very knowledgable in what they do.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "We are professionals.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "But debtors are not stupid and should be expected to do their own research and educate themselves to participate in their defense.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "Why should a creditor have to explain to a debtor how to avoid paying their debt.", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "policy", "text": "By the time it's reached litigation, those conversations should have already occured", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "policy", "text": "and the debtor should be ready to offer his defense without being \"taught\" by the person to whom he owes money.", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "686", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "Debt collectors file a large number of default judgments ", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "because quite simply consumers do not take action, not because they are unaware of the issue.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "Usually at the time a lawsuit is filed, a debt collector has attempted to resolve the issue via telephone calls and/or letters.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "This doesn't even include the efforts the original creditor may have made.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "A lawsuit is never a first response.", "reasons": ["5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "It is usually done after numerous and repeated failed efforts to work with a consumer to resolve an outstanding debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "A default judgment is just a further extension of that.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "Even after we file suit, we may attempt to reach the consumer to resolve the lawsuit prior to judgment being taken.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have seen numerous files where we have spoken to the consumer and told them they can file an answer, and they still don't.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "In my opinion, default judgments are largely the result of consumer's deliberate uninvolvement with the process, rather than a collector taking deceptive steps.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "value", "text": "I will state that many states have local rules that if there is no response to a summons and the consumer has defaulted, they do not need to be noticed on a motion for a default judgment.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "value", "text": "Therefore, the actual entry of the judgment may in fact come as a surprise, despite the summons stating if you don't answer a judgment may be taken.", "reasons": ["10"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "value", "text": "However, an attorney who follows the local rules is not acting deceptively.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 13, "type": "value", "text": "In order to curb this shock for the consumer who doesn't answer, it wouldn't be bad to require all motions for judgment be served upon the consumer, despite local rules which may require otherwise.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 14, "type": "value", "text": "I would point out, many default judgment motions are not noticed for motion hour.", "reasons": ["15"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 15, "type": "value", "text": "They may simply be submitted for a ruling without a court hearing.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 16, "type": "fact", "text": "As to the inquiry as to what is required to support a default judgment, this varies court to court and judge to judge.", "reasons": null, "evidence": ["17"]}, {"id": 17, "type": "testimony", "text": "The courts that I have seen require more documentation are largely looking for affidavits of debt, charge off statements and statement showing payments or charges, and the assignment (if the plaintiff is a debt buyer).", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "996", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "Dan says that the \"Telephone Consumer Protection Act (TCPA) prohibits creditors from using automated dialing systems to call cell phone numbers without consent from the customer\"", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "and that sounds reasonable if that were true.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "I receive countless ro-bo calls on my cell, to which most never leave a message ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "so there is no way to report it.", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "To add to that, I have sent written notice to all creditors not to call my cell because of the charges, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "testimony", "text": "yet someone is calling.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "testimony", "text": "I do not answer those unknown calls ", "reasons": ["7"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "because I have nothing more to add to any previous calls about the debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "testimony", "text": "The only call that has ever left a message is about a debt for someone else, too which I called and told them ithey have the wrong number and not to call, but they still call.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1257", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "As there can be a substantial monetary impact from incorrect entries on a credit report in the form of higher interest rates or being unable to secure a loan,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "bonafide disputes should NOT be allowed on a credit report.", "reasons": ["0"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1140", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "When a debt collection company (Bayview) took over servicing of my mortgage, I began receiving phone calls at work and on my cell phone about my mortgage payments", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "even thought they were not late.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "This included robo-calls.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "I was told this was 'standard' and to ignore these phone calls,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "but I really got angry and filed a BBB complaint in the state of one office.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "testimony", "text": "I was never late with one payment,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "testimony", "text": "and our mortgage was not in debt collection.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "fact", "text": "Bayview may be a debt collector,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "policy", "text": "but they need to keep those services separate from their mortgage services.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "policy", "text": "Calling people at work, robo-calls, and harassing them when they do not have delinquent debts should be against the law.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "312", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "In most states all that a debt collection law office needs to provide is a complaint.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "The average consumer has no idea what the difference is between a balance and a sum.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "they do not know how to calculate the interest and certainly do not know what is \"legal\" pursuant to state or Federal Credit Card Act limitations.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "The name of the Plaintiff may not even be recognizable to them.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "They just know that they owed some money and fell behind on bills.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "More times than not, they do not respond at all.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "793", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I found an unsealed envelope in my mail box that had court documents in them.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "I contacted the debt collection company and asked what was going on ", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "since I had not been served.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "They claimed a subservice had already been done to someone at my residence.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "I explained that was probably not likely ", "reasons": ["5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "testimony", "text": "because I am a Caregiver and I would have been the only one to answer the door and I did not get any service.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "testimony", "text": "I had to pay to file a response and was late by one day, andthen had to challenge the default because of the non service.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "testimony", "text": "The judge agreed that there had been no valid subservice ", "reasons": ["8"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "testimony", "text": "based on the fact that the service company used the most generic \"guess\" they could come up with, a women in her mid 30's to late 40's, around 5 foot 4 inches, weight around 130 pounds to 150 pounds.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "That is about as generic of a description as one could give, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "testimony", "text": "and it was completely wrong.", "reasons": ["11"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "testimony", "text": "because that person did not exist.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "testimony", "text": "They even made up a name of someone I had never heard of and when I googled the name, could not find it anywhere on the internet.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 13, "type": "value", "text": "The second time a false subservice happened, a very similar description was given as the first time, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 14, "type": "testimony", "text": "and the alleged subservice recipient was identified as \"Jane Doe\".", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 15, "type": "value", "text": "I would like to point how dangerous these lies are on another level.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 16, "type": "testimony", "text": "I exclusively have been providing CareGiving services for my parents, no one else has.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 17, "type": "value", "text": "By lying and introducing these lies into a court document, anytime in the future I could be accused of exposing my parents to a person at our residence who never even existed.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 18, "type": "value", "text": "I was also somewhat frozen by this level of dishonesty", "reasons": ["19"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 19, "type": "testimony", "text": "because on the rare occasion when I had to sue someone, I followed the law and had the service performed legally and properly.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 20, "type": "value", "text": "I just expected the same in return", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 21, "type": "value", "text": "and by not getting it weakens one's ability to respond.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1142", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "The agency I work for is small and follows FDCPA to the letter of the law.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "And yet we are still sued constantly by attorneys representing debtors.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "These attorneys count on the fact that it's less costly to settle than to go to court to prove that we have not violated the law.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "Our retail division is in trouble", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "because we've recently lost our two largest clients -- for this reason.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "They're now getting slapped with bogus lawsuits as well.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "People don't even have to pay their bills any more;", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "they just send a \"cease and desist\" letter, hire an attorney, and wait for a settlement to roll in.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "All this will lead to are more stringent rules around extending credit, which is not a good thing for the economy.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "If we keep going down this slope, the only people who will be able to get credit will be those who don't need it.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1079", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "I would like to see the CFPB address the issue of their \"phishing\" expeditions , i.e., trolling the phone listings and calling anyone with a similar name.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "I was listed by my initials, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "but with a common last name, I was getting daily calls from debt collectors until I switched my listing to a nickname.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "There are many comments on this site from people having the same problem,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "so it's obviously a common practice.", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "testimony", "text": "For some strange reason, the folks in the phone centers, react badly when I ask them to explain how my phone number ended up being programmed into their robo dialer.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "testimony", "text": "The usual response has been to hang up on me.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "policy", "text": "I would also like to see the CFPB address the issue of repeated calls to the wrong person.", "reasons": ["8"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "If I'm not the person of interest on the first call, then I won't be on any subsequent calls.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "In my experience with debt collectors, I have reached the conclusion that their are two reasons for repeatedly calling me:", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "fact", "text": "The people in the call centers are trained not to take No for an answer.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "value", "text": "By calling me repeatedly the debt collector is trying to wear me down and get me to pay a debt that isn't mine just to get them to stop calling.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1417", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I respectfully disagree with your assessment.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "If anything, I believe that a national statute of limitations would actually stop the process of zombie debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "We live in a transient society.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "Assume that a national SOL were to be adapted\"", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "Also, you did not address the issue of tolling.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "Again, we live in a transient society.", "reasons": ["6"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "fact", "text": "People move from place to place.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "testimony", "text": "For example, I had a medical crisis in Illinois.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "testimony", "text": "I was not able to keep up with the debt. ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "testimony", "text": "I moved back to my home state of Wisconsin in a town 25 miles away from the Illinois border.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "testimony", "text": "Now, because I live in Wisconsin, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "testimony", "text": "the SOL has passed ", "reasons": ["10"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "testimony", "text": "and I can no longer be sued here.", "reasons": ["11"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 13, "type": "value", "text": "However, should I ever choose to move back to Illinois (which I can't unless I want my credit destroyed and want to get sued) it\"s as though the debt never went away due to their tolling laws and longer SOL.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 14, "type": "value", "text": "It seems that the rationale behind your argument is to solely protect those people who live in states with short SOLs (3-4 years).", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 15, "type": "fact", "text": "That\"s not even 50 %.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 16, "type": "value", "text": "A reasonable universal statute of limitations would make things more clear.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 17, "type": "policy", "text": "At the very least, tolling provisions should be eliminated should states have their own statute of limitations.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "790", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Clear communication helps everyone, not just consumers.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "I think debt collectors when trying to collect just send bills,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "and everyone knows what a bill is.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "But when they devolve into harassment, they blur the lines between trying to collect debt within the law and behaving in misleading and abusive ways toward consumers.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "TRuly, the robot calling, the letters, they have money enough for this.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "If they communicated clearly up front, they would save more money.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "The post office is still a good deal,", "reasons": ["7"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "not an expensive way to communicate.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "You are missing the boat on the problem, though.", "reasons": ["9"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "It is not the costs or whether they should communicate.", "reasons": ["10"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "value", "text": "Most of these companies hire people who are barely literate, poorly trained and certainly uninformed -- wait, UNINFORMED -- about the laws that already exist regarding debt collection.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "value", "text": "That is a huge problem when trying to get information from an employee who doesn't know the law requires him/her to provide certain information.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "value", "text": "This has come about from decades of lack of oversight, in my opinion.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 13, "type": "value", "text": "Lack of oversight, lack of clear rules and lack of enforcement.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 14, "type": "value", "text": "So, if they don't have to worry about following the law, they hire whoever they can cheap and don't bother to train them.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 15, "type": "value", "text": "This is why there are so many of these companies", "reasons": ["14"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 16, "type": "value", "text": "and after some of them do get in trouble, they just change their name and keep on doing the same law-breaking habits.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "485", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "The problem is that cell phone customers have to pay for the minutes that are used.", "reasons": ["1_2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have pre paid cell service ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "and debt collectors are calling me all the time looking for someone else who I do not know.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "This is the problem.", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "Harassment to the cell phone owner and harassment that the cell phone owner must pay for.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "this is why it will always remain illegal for debt collectors to call cell phones.", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1369", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "There needs to be a universal Statute of Limitations.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "The current system is an absolute mess.", "reasons": ["2_3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "17 states maintain a SOL of three to four years, while 19 others have the six years SOL time limit.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "The rest all have diverse SOL limits with some extending for even up to 10 years.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "Tolling provisions make it even more confusing.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "policy", "text": "Simplify it.", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "policy", "text": "Have a single NATIONAL Statute of Limitations.", "reasons": ["9"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "policy", "text": "Make it fair for everyone (debt collectors and debtors", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "5 years seems reasonable.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "Having a universal Statute of Limitations will eliminate confusion and ambiguity as to when and where a debtor can be sued.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "348", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Notifying consumers of the sale of their debts and related details would help consumers with identifying who is contacting them about a debt;", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "there are robo calls about lowering your credit card interest rate and such that are solicitations.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "Consumers have a right to know who they are dealing with in relation to their financial affairs.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "362", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "I should know if a debt is time-barred,", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "so that I can make an informed decision regarding the debt in question.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "The information should be in the validation notice.", "reasons": ["0"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "If the debt becomes time-barred after the validation notice is sent, I should be informed of the new status of the debt IMMEDIATELY!", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "354", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "This kind of thing is likely determined by family court law in the jurisdiction where the debtor lives.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "Community property law, divorce or separation agreements and issues of domestic violence laws all come into play in these kinds of circumstances.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1274", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I would take a hard look at 'credit reporting' from what is being reported by a creditor and then what is reported by a debt collection or debt buying company.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "For example, if a creditor obtains a judgment amount greater than the account balance, that amount is likely not reported ", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "because creditors seldom have system capabilities to make adjustments to accounts.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "505", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I don't think limiting the time to call a person at work is an option.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "Everyone works at different times.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "Some people moves, change cell phone numbers , ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "so call them at work is sometimes the only option.", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "It's hard to know what place \"prefers\" no personal calls , ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "and a list could be an option, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "fact", "text": "but most people work for smaller company's ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "and the lists will cater to the large company's.", "reasons": ["6"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "fact", "text": "Most people have information about where they work somewhere on the web.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "I don't see a problem if a debt collector calls a customer at work if they don't know prior of any inconvenience.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "825", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "A dialer does none of the things to which you refer.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "A human takes a lists of calls that are deemed restricted to any of the criteria that you listed,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "and loads that list into the computer software that also holds a lists of all calls to be made.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "Then the list of restricted calls are \"scrubbed\" out of the automated dialer.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "This scrubbing process is akin to a human scratching out a phone number with a pen on a paper list.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "There are no measurable gains in consumer protection to which you refer.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "fact", "text": "Calls are not recorded through the dialer.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "fact", "text": "Dialers work in unison with the recording software.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "fact", "text": "This recording software records manual phone calls just the same.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1213", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "You are absolutely right.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "But, you'd be surprised at how many times this does happen and how many times the Credit Bureaus Do change correct information to false information supplied by the 'furnisher/debt collector'.", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "Because I had to send in numerous Certified Letter to the Credit Bureaus, (all of them), in order to stay on top of all the false information and tricks that they did supply.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "And I have written proof, that this does and is still happening to other consumers, right now.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1125", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have never applied for credit in any way other by paper application,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "and everyone I have ever owed money to has tons of paperwork.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "I don't know how it works when you apply electronically,", "reasons": ["0", "1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "but what's to prevent someone from saying they are owed money?", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "The burden of proof is going to have to be on the creditor,", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "and if they aren't getting paper signatures, they'd better have some pretty good proof otherwise.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "Meanwhile, if you say they wouldn't lie about it, I would love to sell you my ocean front property in Nebraska.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1014", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "Attorneys are not exempted from the FDCPA, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "and most State Bars take reports of unethical conduct by attorneys very seriously.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "There is no need for additional regulation of attorneys.", "reasons": ["0", "1"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "347", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "Consumers should be made aware of sale or transfer of their debts.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "From whom to whom along with effective dates and contact info for the creditor and the new owner of the debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "336", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "Bank of America, my mortgage holder, does NOT even allow a formal dispute to move forward.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "The past 12 months have been a continues headache with Bank of America.", "reasons": ["2_4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "For example, our mortgage account have always been current, and never were we in Foreclosure status, nor even approaching default.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "However, every single month Bank of America reported to the three major credit bureaus that we were late.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "I've worked with their Military Liaison Officer on the resolution through phone calls, email messages, and formal letters but without success.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "policy", "text": "Urgent Help/Assistance is needed for consumers to navigate and to resolve the problems that Bank of America is creating over simple and elementary issues of basic accounting procedures.", "reasons": ["6", "7"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "Bank of America has the undue power of making reports to the credit bureaus which adversely affects the consumer.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "The Consumer lacks tools to challenge and fight back on Bank of America's abuse of power.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "582", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "Actually there should always be more communication about specific things, rather than less.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "More communication from the Original Creditors that an account will be turned over to a collector and when.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "And when a debt collector then turns it over or sells to someone else there should be more communication about who.", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "Just like when mortgages are sold to other servicers, the borrowers get letters informing them of who now owns their mortgage and who now to send payment to.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "policy", "text": "This should be standard practice for debt collectors.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "policy", "text": "Explaining to the debtor that they have turned the account to someone else and that all payment and communication should now be directed to the new guy (even if no payments were sent to the first debt collector.", "reasons": ["7"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "Because there are debtors who can't make payment now but can later, and if they start sending payment to an old debt collector via an old letter they got in the mail, then debtors attempts to actually resolve the debt go by the wayside.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "More communication about who/what/where/how is necessary.", "reasons": ["6"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "365", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I do not believe that it would have mattered.", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "It seemed that the Attorney/debt collector was not looking for the actual debtor", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "I believe that all that they were trying to do was to make a quick buck.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "They did a couple of shady things with this case.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "policy", "text": "For a solution; the laws should be written so the common lay person can understand.", "reasons": ["5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "If I had known that a validation request would not be considered I would not have wasted my time and paid even though it was NOT my debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1256", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "Collectors should be barred from stating that payment of a debt will definitively improve a consumers credit score ", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "as FICO (the industry standard) uses proprietary algorithm that the collection agent cannot possibly guess at.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "Yes, a collection agent, in good faith negotiation for resolution of the alleged debt should be able to remove the collection trade line from the consumers credit reports which should be stipulated in a binding settlement agreement signed by both parties.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "872", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "Periodically (probably when the debt has been sold) I receive harassing phone calls from collection companies regarding a believed debt that my nephew owes.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "I send him Christmas cards annually, see him at family gatherings every 5 years or so, and stopped contacting him about this harassment after he assured me it had already been taken care of when I received my first call.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "These calls happen about once a year for a couple weeks at a time.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1399", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I got hit with a notice from a doctor's office and his collection agency that I owed and -- get this -- never responded to their notices.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "First, I never got any notices ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "and second, I called the doctor's office and validated that I have never been a patient there.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "The office manager even wrote a letter to the collection agency.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "It was clearly THEIR mistake,", "reasons": ["0_1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "The collection agency got all hot and bothered and rude to me", "reasons": ["6"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "testimony", "text": "because then they had to pay to remove the notice of me \"owing\" a debt from the three credit reporting agencies", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "boy I hope you go after these cowboys next -- ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "testimony", "text": "and yet it was removed.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "testimony", "text": "But while waiting for the letter, I managed to actually get someone on the phone from Equifax,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "value", "text": "I was so angry, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "value", "text": "and their attitude was, \"we just report this\" blah blah blah.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "policy", "text": "I say there ought to be sanctions, monetary sanctions, against these credit reporting agencies for making these mistakes and their cavalier attitude.", "reasons": ["10"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 13, "type": "value", "text": "They have this attitude of, so what?", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 14, "type": "value", "text": "This has been more than two years ago and still seethe because of the cavalier and rude attitude when it was clearly their mistake.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 15, "type": "testimony", "text": "I even called MY eye doctor and had him write a letter that I was HIS patient.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 16, "type": "value", "text": "You think things don't get out of hand?", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 17, "type": "value", "text": "YOu don't know how this kind of thing hurts people's ratings, scores whatever and then add insult to injury when you deal with rude inept people.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 18, "type": "policy", "text": "Hit them in the pocketbook and you will see how fast they will make sure they do not make any mistakes.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "768", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "Debt collectors should announce themselves and refrain from acting like: investigators, attorneys, or hitmen.", "reasons": ["2_7"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "There needs to be an enforced code of behavior that represents a professional on the other end of the phone.", "reasons": ["0", "2_7"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "Most recently, my husband has been receiving threatning phone calls from a collector pretending to be a law enforcement investigator.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "The most humiliating part is that the calls have escalated to his ex-wife, cousin, and associates.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "He has a common name and the \"investigator\" has not properly identified himself or clearly identified if my husband is the right person that the debt belongs too.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "testimony", "text": "In addition, the so called debt is 8 yrs old,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "testimony", "text": "and they call from unknown numbers", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "testimony", "text": "or if the number shows up and it's googled there are comments stating that the persons calling are harassing.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "669", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I think I do kind of like this idea.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "This designated database/website could also list Summary of Rights for state laws and Fed laws.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "Then this same website might also be able to be used as a way to report abusive behaviors (or link to the appropriate websites to do so), and other relevant information for consumers regarding consumer debt, credit, and credit reports, and other various useful information that is currently available but is spread across many agency websites.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "The website could be paid for and maintained by the debt collectors (sort of like how annualcreditreport.com is paid for and maintained by the credit reporting agencies).", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "It could be a way to help bring legitimacy to the debt collection industry by having a way to identify them to separate the legit companies from the bad ones while allowing collectors to operate effectively.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1028", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "The FICO impact on sold debts appearing twice needs to be addressed with the credit reporting agencies and the companies that create credit scores.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "Creditors have a right to report the status of a debt, and shouldn't be precluded just because it already appears by the previous creditor.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "However, the double penalty against the consumer is certainly unfair.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "But it's not the collectors' fault.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "policy", "text": "It should be addressed in enforcement of the FCRA.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1091", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "Any FTC rule regarding verification should absolutely include an exception for frivolous and irrelevant disputes", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "because there are way too many websites out there providing sample dispute letters and the advice to keep using them that the process is abused by enough debtors that we now have a standard letter to address this issue.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1012", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "Many states currently have laws that make it illegal to engage in debt collection without being licensed to do so in the state.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "However, this does not stop debt collectors from violating these state laws and threatening to sue individuals,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "even though they legally cannot ", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "because they are unlicensed in the state.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "This is unlawful and menacing behavior.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "It would be easier to bring claims under the FDCPA if the act were more clear that threats to sue when a debt collector is unlicensed to collect on a debt in a state is a false, deceptive, or misleading representation.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "This clarity combined with stronger penalties might serve to better dissuade debt collectors from continuing to violate the law in attempts to collect on debts in state where they have no right to.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "986", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "As a former bill collector for over 17 years there are alot of ways the industry needs to be cleaned up.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "I do believe that a debtor should be informed of when a debt is transfered from original creditor to a collector and whether or not that collection agency purchased the debt or if the agency is contracted by the original creditor to collect the debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "There is a big misconception that I see being made in most of these comments that everything is \"purchased\" which is far from the truth!", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "I personally have not and would not work for an agency that purchased debt,", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "because I know and have heard the horror stories of not only how they treat the debtor but also how the business as a whole treats the collector.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1208", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "It might help to take a look at how debt collectors are compensated.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "I think, based upon people I know who have held such work, that collectors who receive their pay based on a commission are incentivized to abuse the consumer.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "I do not think the CFPB's mission is to provide job security for the debt collection industry.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1209", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Marian makes an excellent point about how Debt Collectors are paid.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "They try to get as much money upfront as possible.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "Ironically, if they get too much money upfront, the credit card company might snatch the account back from the debt collector.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "If the amount is \"too low\" that the debt collector receives, they are not interested.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "This goes against many sales principles that it is easier to interact at a later date with a paying customer versus trying to make a big score all at once.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "745", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "My deceased daughter(she passed 2 years ago) had some debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "We continue to receive calls from debt collectors even after we have asked them not to call us anymore.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "My wife has filed complaints with the Oregon State Justice dept. to complain about the harrassment.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "Why can't these collectors do their research on the debtor, before they harrass the parents!!", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "205", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Assignments without notice could lead to consumers paying the wrong person.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "The CFPB should encourage proper notice by ruling that a payment made to either of the assignee or the assignor reduces the debt.", "reasons": ["0"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "400", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I did the same thing ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "and the response was immediate to stop the abusive behaviors.", "reasons": null, "evidence": ["2", "3"]}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "Like you most debt collectors just hang up.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "Those who stayed on immediately changed their tone of voice and behavior.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "I would advise anyone receiving verbally abusive, harassing, or threatening phone calls from debt collection calls buy a cheap telephone recording device and to use it when they call.", "reasons": ["0_1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "policy", "text": "When they inform you at the mini-Miranda point interrupt them and tell them that you too are now recording all debt collection calls.", "reasons": ["6"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "It's the most powerful tool any debtor can use.", "reasons": ["0_1"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "943", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "Since the UCC and to the best of my knowledge, State laws do not define reasonable period of time,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "this is a problem and has been a problem for most lenders and third party collectors based on me experience of over 40 years.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "Consumers should be able to seek assistance from an attorney", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "and be required to provide the attorney contact information to a collector, unless the attorney has not already.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "policy", "text": "The attorney should be required to notify all creditors of representation within 20 business days of the consumer's signed agreement of that representation.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "fact", "text": "While most attorneys do notify lenders and/or third party agencies some do not and some do not respond to inquiries concerning representation.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "policy", "text": "After the first lender/third party inquiry the attorney should be required to notify the lender and/or agency within 10 business days in writing of representation.", "reasons": ["5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "policy", "text": "The attorney should be required to notify a lender and/or third party within 7 business days that representation of the debtor has been terminated.", "reasons": ["5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "policy", "text": "It should not be a violation for a lender or third party to contact the debtor after 30 days to only determine if the debtor has continued representation of an attorney if there has been no communication provided by the attorney after 30 days of the initial notification in writing of representation.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have experienced no communication after the initial notice by the debtor and/or attorney received over 60-90 days and even six months.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "policy", "text": "If non profit credit counseling agencies can send notification to lenders and third party collectors for representation of a consumer to reduce payments after an initial meeting I believe attorneys should be able to notify in the time periods specified.", "reasons": ["11"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "value", "text": "Setting rules of notification time frames would benefit all parties.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1169", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "Recently I received an \"offer\" from a firm indicating it would approve a new Visa or MasterCard account if I agreed to assume responsibility for a debt allegedly owed to another credit card firm.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "The first firm, which apparently was the original creditor, apparently sold the alleged debt to a third party.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "It was this third party that was making the \"offer\" to open a new credit account.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "Of course, there was a \"hook.\"", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "If I agreed to assume financial responsibility for the alleged debt and if the third party opened the new account, the credit limit would be for the alleged debt plus a significant \"service charge\" for the transaction.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "testimony", "text": "The finance charge was listed at 29%.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "Another questionable aspect of the matter was no guarantee a credit line would remain open as the account was paid down.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "Thus, if the initial \"credit line\" was $500 to cover the outstanding debt and service fee, as the balance were paid down and/or off, the credit limit could be decreased", "reasons": ["8"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "so as to prevent it from being used for new purchases.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "testimony", "text": "Obviously, I shredded the \"offer\" package", "reasons": ["10"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "testimony", "text": "as I did not owe the initial debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "value", "text": "I wonder how many people will consider this a relief of some type and agree to the \"offer.\"", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "472", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I agree.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "I've heard of this happening ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "and it's unjust.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1154", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have had several doctor/laboratory debts placed on my credit report.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "These are debts that I never rec'd a bill for or even a phone call from the hospital or facility.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have very good health insurance that paid over $14k when I had my baby...", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "3 months go by and I start getting notified by my credit monitoring agency that my credit score is going down.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "things such as a (pediatric audiology test $83) when my baby was 1 day old.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "fact", "text": "apparently the audiologist doesnt bill through the hospital....", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "fact", "text": "subsequently, they also dont bill the patients..", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "fact", "text": "they outsource their billing to a 3rd party collection agency who immediately reports it to all 3 credit bureaus.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "Maybe i missed that forumn on this sight,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "testimony", "text": "A company can send a $100 bill to Transunion and say I owe it, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "testimony", "text": "and BAM...my credit score takes a 10 point dive.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "policy", "text": "Agencies should not be able to put something on your credit report without first having not only validated the debt and provided any and all documents that prove you owe the debt, but they must be required to have attempted to collect the debt.", "reasons": ["9_10"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have had businesses tell em that its cheaper to put the bill directly on your credit report than it is to hire a 3rd party to collect the debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 13, "type": "value", "text": "This is a horrible injustice to the people who pay their bills, maintain health iunsurance and who will pay their outstanding debts.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 14, "type": "value", "text": "The system is set up to force the consumer to prove their innocence (if you will) verus the creditor proving they are owed a debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "763", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I am sure many judges would disagree with you.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "Courtrooms are not a playground.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "And judges do not like it when plaintiffs waste their time by filling frivolous lawsuits that do not have proof.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "530", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I dont mind the calls to work.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "My problem is the frequency.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "The reality is that I owe the bill and I know it.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "But I dont think they should call my job unless I dont call them back.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "policy", "text": "Tect me and call me first and give me a few days.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "policy", "text": "Then call my job but not every day.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "963", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "The burden of proof cannot be placed anywhere else, JClark53.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "But, a disputed account is rare.", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "Most people are aware of their obligations, but just cannot pay them now.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "Starting the process should be simple and clear to each party, not talk about judgments or disputes where it is unlikely that either apply.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1078", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "State regulations should preempt them from collecting exorbitant returns on such minimal investment (usury!!!).", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "Other items to consider pertaining to this issue are : The bad debt", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "buyer does not disclose what he/she purchased the bad debt for.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "This should be disclosed and transparent", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "as they have the original debt information, including SSN, phone and financial information.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "I don't begrudge them making a profit ,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "policy", "text": "but their predatory practices need to be regulated.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "policy", "text": "A superior court judge should be able to examine the original transaction,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "policy", "text": "all the documents concerning the purchase of this debt by a third party and determine a fair and equitable payment to resolve the problem, avoiding bankruptcy .", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "987", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "It is mind-boggling that this has even been allowed to continue for so long.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "This should have been addressed years ago!", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "Stop allowing the company to change names to continue poor practices.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "Stop allowing the companies to use hundreds of phone numbers to try to trick someone.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "policy", "text": "Stop letting them block numbers so caller ID only shows \"unknown\" or even 000-0000.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "policy", "text": "Stop putting the burden of stopping this entire industry on the consumer (who has no teeth or way to be sure the judgment is being enforced", "reasons": ["6", "8"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "THAT IS THE JOB OF CONSUMER PROTECTION!", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "fact", "text": "It's in your name!", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "You are there to PROTECT the CONSUMER.", "reasons": ["6"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "policy", "text": "Force these companies to properly identify themselves when asked!", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "testimony", "text": "Debt collectors have been calling my cell phone for 5 years trying to collect a debt from someone I have never heard of.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "testimony", "text": "This random person put down my phone number as a contact on a loan, defaulted on that loan, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "testimony", "text": "and now i am the one being harassed because of a stranger!", "reasons": ["11"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 13, "type": "testimony", "text": "When called and they identify who they are looking for, i used to say that i did not know the person then try to ask for the name of the company, but they had already hung up on me and would then call again later.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 14, "type": "testimony", "text": "So then, after they ask for the person, I immediately ask for the name and address for the company.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 15, "type": "testimony", "text": "They would ask again for \"name,\" I would ask again for the name and address for the company.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 16, "type": "testimony", "text": "They would ask again for \"name,\" ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 17, "type": "testimony", "text": "I would ask again for the name and address for the company.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 18, "type": "testimony", "text": "It becomes a shouting match, they say \"I'll just call back later when you are in a more 'information giving' mood,\" and hang up on me.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 19, "type": "testimony", "text": "There was/is no recourse, protection, or help for people like me.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 20, "type": "testimony", "text": "The company won't give me their name and I don't have a phone number (because it is \"unknown\") to give to the regulating bodies to report harassing behavior.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 21, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have no way to stop these people from calling my cell phone!", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 22, "type": "testimony", "text": "It is my phone!", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 23, "type": "testimony", "text": "I pay the bill, not them!", "reasons": ["22"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 24, "type": "policy", "text": "They should have no \"RIGHT\" as they put it to call a cell phone!", "reasons": ["22", "23"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "599", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I absolutely hate robocalls, especially those that repeat constantly and relentlessly.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "There are some people who shirk their responsibilities,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "but there are also those who simply do not have money to pay out a debt.", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "People lose their jobs, get laid off, get sick and can't work, retire and try to make it from one month to the next on miniscule retirement benefits.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "policy", "text": "There should be a regulation against robocalls, period.", "reasons": ["7"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "policy", "text": "They should not be allowed.", "reasons": ["7"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "They are not necessary and only serve to harass people.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "It's a bullying tactic, in my opinion.", "reasons": ["6"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "784", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I concur with previous comment.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "If consumers are informed when our mortgages are sold that should be a rule across the board.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "Sending a letter by mail isn't very expensive, either.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "It should contain the amount, info on original debt, the name and address of who owns the debt and I'd even add the amount the debt was sold for.", "reasons": ["4", "5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "Consumers can keep track for one thing, and make sure these debts are not posted twice on our credit reports,", "reasons": ["5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "it will let people know who to contact about the debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "794", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "The data is difficult to obtain", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "and likely not attainable", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "considering lawsuits can be filed in magistrate, county, state, and federal courts.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "Also the data could be inaccurate", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "since a case can be postponed and renewed later.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "I do not know if there is any central data base for either court.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "fact", "text": "Also, lawsuits are filed in bankruptcy proceedings as well", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "so these would need to be considered as well.", "reasons": ["6"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "This is why I am concerned when numbers just get tossed out without and substance verification.", "reasons": ["0_1", "3", "6_7"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "Based on my experiences I would estimate about 1.5% of delinquent accounts were forwarded to filing a lawsuit.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "549", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "A debt that is paid in full doesn't improve a credit score at all.", "reasons": null, "evidence": ["6"]}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "A debt that is settled for less or paid in full is the exact same.", "reasons": null, "evidence": ["6"]}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "Once the damage is done to a credit score, the damage will remain.", "reasons": ["0", "1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "The only slight (very small) improvement on a credit score is when a bad debt was a credit card account and had over 100% utilization.", "reasons": null, "evidence": ["6"]}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "Once the utilization goes down below 100% (and that occurs when the credit card debt was either settled for less or paid in full) does the credit score improve only very slightly.", "reasons": null, "evidence": ["6"]}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "But the damage is still done and will take years to recover from.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "reference", "text": "http://www.myfico.com/CreditEducation/ImproveYourScore.aspx", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "573", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "That is not going to work.", "reasons": ["1", "2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "The burden of proof in the American Justice System is bore by the one who is making the accusations.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "Some debtors are going to lie and say that a debt is not theirs when it actually is,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "but that is the nature of the beast with debt collections.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "Innocent until proven guilty is the rules of the game.", "reasons": ["5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "Otherwise I, as a debt collector, can accuse anyone of anything owning any amount and extort money from innocent people.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "Debt collection is about collecting debt, not about making accusations and extortions.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "596", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I contacted the debt collection company and tried to make arrangements for payment of debt,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "the reason I could not pay my bills is my husband was laid off work and he had started a new job.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "I wanted to make payments of $100. a month, debt collectors said NO, so I said the most I could afford was $200 a month the said NO they wanted $1,000. a month.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "Now we have 4 children, a mortgage and utility payment, debt collection said $500 a month my husband brought home after taxes $1,100 twice a month.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "My mortgage is $1,300 per month not including utilizes so I told debt company that I couldn't pay.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "I always thought something was better than nothing and that a debt company would try to work with you.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "I learned that they won't work with you.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "628", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "Creditors should only be allowed to call between the hours of 9am until 7pm local time unless they have written consent (maybe even a web form) that gives them a minimum 3 hour window in which to call.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "Additionally, they are limited to 3 phone calls a day maximum.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "If they leave a message they should be required to leave the name of the company, the name of the representative, the number to call, and a reference number.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "In regards to debt sales, the entity selling the debt should give 90 days notice of the intent to sell giving the consumer notification of the intent to sell and maybe even offer a settlement amount.", "reasons": ["5_12"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "policy", "text": "The entity purchasing the debt must honor any and all terms of the debt they are purchasing (i.e. payment plans, deferment/forbearance, etc.).", "reasons": ["5_12"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "testimony", "text": "My brother has several private student loans.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "testimony", "text": "About a year ago we started getting phone calls from Discover in regards to student loans and we all assumed that it was a sales call because no one living at my address had student loans with them.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "testimony", "text": "Eventually we managed to be home when they called ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "testimony", "text": "and we discovered that two of my brother's loans were sold to Discover ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "testimony", "text": "and he was never notified.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "testimony", "text": "So all this time thinking it was a sales call, because Discover only gave a 1-800 number to call about student loans and not even the name of the person they were trying to reach, his loans were actually in default ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "testimony", "text": "because Discover cancelled the forbearance he had upon purchase.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "testimony", "text": "When he attempted to put them back into forbearance, Discover told him they \"didn't have a system for that yet\".", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "413", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "The idea is sound in principle,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "but as any technology geared towards convienance, there are risks against privacy encouraging identity theft.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "Having creditors, collectors, and consumers come together \"on the same page\" regarding debt would be fantastic for everyone involved.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "But any technology which accomplishes this needs to be very secure with very strict authentication requirements to ensure *only* the relevant parties can view information concerning the debt.", "reasons": ["4_5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "Otherwise, not only thieves would have access to this information", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "but also non-criminal third parties, who may never have learned of such information due to the protection of consumer privacy laws.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "policy", "text": "Knowledge of the debt and money owed would need to have the same level of security afforded to consumer reports and information within a consumer report (as defined in the FCRA).", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "460", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "jfearon, I think you have to do it online.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "I was able to clean up a family member's credit report online.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1172", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "Some years ago, a debt collector was trying to collect a debt for an emergency room visit that included foot/leg xrays.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "The problem was that the only time I had ever been to the hospital in question was a worker's compensation covered workplace injury and it involved only my hand (sliced open, six stitches).", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "I had contacted the collection agency and informed them that I did not owe anything and the circumstances of the visit.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "Although that did not work, once I contacted all three credit bureaus with the same information, the debt collector was unable to verify the debt", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "and they removed it from my credit report - and stopped contacting me.", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "975", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I would like to have some protection from the calls I have received over several years from debt collection services looking for a woman who does not live at this address and has never lived at this address.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "I keep getting reassurances that my number will be removed, but the calls continue.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1121", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "If this is an area that the CFPB is interested in regulating, I believe it will be necessary to initiate cooperative actions with local State judiciaries.", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "Because the CFPB is a federal agency,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "it doesn't have authority to tell State governments (including the judicial branch) how to operate or how to interpret its own law.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "Since some states are already taking steps in this direction ( like New York),", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "it is likely that the CFPB would find positive reception toward this effort.", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "But trying to accomplish change through federal rulemaking is not an option in this particular area.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "387", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "Telephonic pretrial-hearings can be scheduled in support of a consumer having to work;", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "times set and or scheduled with a court representative could passify this issue.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1196", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "Items 1 through 10 should all be provided on the validation notice.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "Number 10 specifically should include the Date-of-service or DOS for the medical debt.", "reasons": ["2", "3", "4", "5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "Many consumers do not realize that medical debt goes to collections just like any other consumer debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "They mistakenly believe that their insurance company will resolve the issue.", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "Also with extensive medical bills ( inpatient surgical stay) consumers have professional bills from each physician ( radiology, pathology, etc) in addition to technical component bills for the facility.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "fact", "text": "Many times the consumer never sees these medical providers and either mistakes the bill for another aspect of the service rendered or, again, just assumes the bill/debt will \"be taken care of\".", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "additionally the name of the consumer's insurance Co./plan on the validation notice would be quite helpful.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "This may seem to be a great deal of extra information", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "fact", "text": "but the originating physician and/or facility obtain this information at the time of or prior to service.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1199", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "My husband called a creditor about payments to an old account and wanted to make the account current after missed payments, due to job loss.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "The account was reopened under a new account number.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "Now I have 2 accounts on my credit report with the same amount.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1112", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "Minors are not normally eligible to enter contracts or take on the obligation of credit arrangements,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "so this would seem necessarily rare.", "reasons": ["0"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "Regardless, every effort should be made and maintained to protect consumers from mistaken disclosure of personal business.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1130", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "Credit bureaus are responsible for 95% of identity theft and inaccurate consumer credit files.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "It's because their revenue comes from businesses who pay for access to their databases including phony ones.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have a letter from a credit bureau that says the only thing they do to investigate/verify accuracy is ask the entity that initially reported the information if it's true.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "New rules have to put tighter restrictions and procedures on credit bureaus", "reasons": ["4", "5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "because they are the root of the actual problem.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "policy", "text": "Secondly, because they are private companies who should not be able to collect or retain any financial information without consumers permission.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "policy", "text": "Submission of proof of debt or other evidence/documents should be required.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "policy", "text": "Retention of the identity of the actual [business] persons reporting the account information should be required.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "policy", "text": "Credit bureaus and debt collectors should not be allowed to sell lists of accounts especially after the accounts are disputed. One creditor, one debt collector.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "policy", "text": "All debt collectors should be required to register on a national database, including phone numbers, that's publicly available online which they must update within 5 business days regarding any changes.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "policy", "text": "All lawyers should not be banned from becoming debt collectors.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "fact", "text": "Here is a a group of people that are trained, licensed in their State, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "value", "text": "but they lie to circumvent the law and the courts.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 13, "type": "value", "text": "At the heart of the mortgage fiasco were unethical lawyers who acted strictly for greed.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 14, "type": "fact", "text": "None of them were prosecuted or disbarred", "reasons": ["15"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 15, "type": "value", "text": "because they hid themselves as representing lenders.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "551", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "As a debt collector, I noticed a problem with the protection of landlords/property owners who are requesting internal DNC's with the company I have employment with.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "As they will be Do not call flagged \"DNC\" with one account, they will not be DNC'ed with another account for the purposes of skip tracing,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "the chance of repeat calls in urban centers harassing certain members of the public is plausible ", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "as the only numbers that are held consistently in the database afaik \"By Law\" are verified and confirmed numbers.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "345", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "Identity Theft Tops List for 13th Consecutive Year in Report of National Consumer Complaints", "reasons": null, "evidence": ["1"]}, {"id": 1, "type": "reference", "text": "http://www.ftc.gov/opa/2013/02/sentineltop.shtm", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1246", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I believe Amex handles this the best.", "reasons": ["1", "2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "The account holder is liable for all charges made by themselves and any authorized users added to the account.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "Authorized Users however are given a unique card number and can be held accountable for any charges they make.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "361", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "If I ever tell a collector that I'm recording the conversation, the call ends rather abruptly or the calls just stop.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "Yet, I'm expected to be recorded whenever they initiate the call.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "They expect me to have an expectation to be recorded when they want to attempt to collect a debt, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "but the minute I want to record them while I dispute a debt, that's out of bounds...", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "331", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I don't think it matters whether a collector used a alias or not.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "It's just a name. If it is used constantly", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "760", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "In fact, it is a gross distortion of the law for the CFPB to claim that suit on a debt outside of the statute of limitations period is per se unfair, deceptive or misleading.", "reasons": ["1_2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "Under the Federal Rules of Civil Procedure (and most state civil rules), the statute of limitations is an affirmative defense which must be pleaded by the defendant;", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "if it is not, the defense is considered to have been waived.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "The purpose of the defense is to enable a party to avoid being disadvantaged by the long delay, loss of evidentiary documents, memory fading, etc.;", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "if the debtor doesn't claim that they are disadvantaged by the delay, then the delay clearly isn't so long as to preclude a vigorous defense.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "411", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "The CFPB should require debt sellers to contact the debtor and inform them the debt has been sold.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "Additionally, ALL pertinent information must be given to the debtor to eliminate any confusion.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "Furthermore, the seller of the debt must be required and enforced to annotate the debtors credit report with the sale to help eliminate confusion and in a way to not increase the bad debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "Essentially, debts that are sold sometimes appear as two seperate debts on a consumers report which increases the penalty of having bad debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "policy", "text": "A consumer should not be penalized twice for 1 debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "912", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have a 20 year plus debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "A couple of times I have refinanced and payed everything on my credit report.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "They never appear until it's over.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "Every year they get a judgement against me ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "and freeze my bank account putting me behind on my bills", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "391", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "The price of paper (bad debt) varies depending on the collectability of the debt based on info known about the debtor and also varies based on the amount of documentation purchased from the original creditor.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "Most debt buyers only pay for a couple of recent credit card statements.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "They may provide a \"bill of sale\"", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "but these never identify a specific account being sold and reference a master purchase contract which is never provided.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1324", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Explaining why the repeat phone call abuse happens does not justify it.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "Apparently there are autodialers that call several consumers at the same time, than hang up on all but the first consumer that answers the phone.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "The result is a person can get several collection calls and hang ups through out the day, ", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "that is just not right.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "675", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Mslade, you have some valid points about the confusing Foti rulings,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "but I think you are wrong about the TCPA.", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "This law has always applied to debt collectors, politicians, and even charities with respect to cellular phones.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "And it's not just one judge who has ruled in this way.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "The FCC and the courts have repeatedly affirmed it.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "226", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "The solution to this problem is a mandate that account numbers and names on them not change during their life, no matter how many times transferred.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "This goes for credit reporting agencies as well.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "479", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "As a bankruptcy lawyer, I frequently deal with clients or are harassed by debt collectors calling family or neighbors.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "the collectors will claim they are acquiring location information, but this is frequently the case where the consumer has been at the same location for years.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "I hope the rules will narrow the \"location information\" exception ", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "so that it can only be used where there is really doubt about the consumer's location.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1411", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "The Permissible hours of 9am - 8 pm is good.", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "I actually would like to see it moved to the other proposed time of 9am - 7pm,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "but i think 8pm is a fair compromise.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "Because the current 8am - 9pm really is just way to early/late.", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "I (and many families) are in bed after 8pm ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "and phone afer 8pm really is way too late.", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "I support the 9am - 8pm hours.", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "I further support weekend calling lessened to noon-5pm ", "reasons": ["8"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "because people like to sleep in on the weekends and spend time with family.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "Having a phone call after 5pm really is not necessary ", "reasons": ["10"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "value", "text": "as most people will be out and/or entertaining guests at their homes and will not take calls in the afternoon.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "value", "text": "I further support adherence to blue laws that prohibit consumer contact on Sundays.", "reasons": ["12"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "value", "text": "Sundays really are when most people are spending whatever little time they have left before the workweek with friends and family.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 13, "type": "testimony", "text": "I do not conduct business on Sundays.", "reasons": ["12"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 14, "type": "policy", "text": "The work week really should be when debt collectors are working on trying to contact consumers.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "373", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I also find the assertion that INVOLUNTARY DEFAULTERS don't put up a legal defense because they are afraid or have a lack of knowledge about the legal system to be outrageous.", "reasons": ["2", "3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "Strategic Defaulters save part of the money that could have gone to pay down their debts so they can give it to an attorney who may be able to get them a sweet pay off deal.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "INVOLUNTARY DEFAULTERS keep trying to make their monthly payments until the monthly accrual of interest rate charges and/or a life changing event forces then into an INVOLUNTARY DEFAULT.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "INVOLUNTARY DEFAULTS are not recognized by the courts.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "I had a SPOTLESS payment record for 15 years prior to a life changing event that caused me to become an unpaid CareGiver.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "If I could have been allowed to start with very small monthly payments to all of my creditors in exchange for having my phone lines left alone, I probably could have started making some income again.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "testimony", "text": "Instead, the constant debt collection phone calls forced me to convert my land lines to 20 cent a minute cell phones that I could not even afford to answer.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "testimony", "text": "I LOST work and contacts", "reasons": ["8"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "testimony", "text": "because debt collectors would not accept small monthly payments as a beginning pathway towards paying off my alleged debt.", "reasons": ["9"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "Probably the ongoing interest rate charges on default debt makes it unrealistic for debt collectors to accept small payments.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "value", "text": "Until alleged defaults are truly frozen so that those who want to pay them off have the best chance to do so, more and more debt will accrue.", "reasons": ["9"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1373", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I agree 100% with this statement.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "Creditors should not simply be able to pull your credit report at their fancy.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "I had so many soft pulls (this was before I realized I needed to opt out of marketing) that my credit report from Equifax got \"split.\"", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "Basically, this means that my report got chopped in half and trade lines disappeared.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "Also, a legitimate creditor attempted to pull my credit and was told by Equifax that I didn't exist.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "testimony", "text": "Everything was GONE.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "testimony", "text": "After numerous fruitless attempts at reaching someone at Equifax, I finally got a real person.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "testimony", "text": "I was informed of the split and told that the burden was on me to provide them with the correct information to \"put my report back together.\"", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "testimony", "text": "I had to fax them my driver's license, social security card, and a utility bill,", "reasons": ["9"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "testimony", "text": "all because their software cracked due to too many inquiries that I didn't even authorize.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "value", "text": "It's still not resolved,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "testimony", "text": "and I've filed a report with the CFPB.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1312", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "Yes...the CFPB should require debt collectors/debt owners to notify consumers in writing, that a payment plan or partial plan will revive the time-barred debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "However, the debt owner or debt collection company should not be allowed to have a second chance to sue you for the old debt.", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "This in itself would be bubble jeopardy in a criminal case of law.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "If anything a second seven year listing of the agreed balance you are willing to repay will be listed on ones credit bureau report would be allowed.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "policy", "text": "Note: A collection company that purchased the account for pennies on the dollar,should \"ONLY\" be allowed to collect the amount of monies they purchased the account for plus any regulated reasonable fee amount.", "reasons": ["5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "fact", "text": "Because they were not the original lender in the first place.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "policy", "text": "The original debt owners should \"ONLY\" be allowed to list the agreed pay off amount of the time-barred account,the consumer agreed to pay.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "Example: debt owner original time-barred account $1.000.00 dollars.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "Debt owner accepts $500.00 and consumer agrees to pay back.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "The only amount to report is the $500.00 dollars.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "757", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "It is unwise to require that the debt collector send sensitive personal information to the debtor (e.g., SSN, account number", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "as such a requirement would expose the debtor to the danger of ID theft.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "956", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I do not communicate with anyone I owe money to by phone.", "reasons": ["1", "3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "I want a written trail.", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "It's too easy for them to say I agreed to something or to give me misleading information by phone.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "I want it IN THE MAIL.", "reasons": ["1", "2"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "631", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "The courts should also mandate that if a debtor has reached out to the creditor in an attempt to negotiate the creditor must continue to try to reach a settlement rather than seeking judgment against the debtor.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "Also, the collection agency should not be able to add interest on top of debt that seek judgment for if the debtor agrees to pay ", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "since they will make a profit over what they paid the original creditor.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "Basically these so called \"attorneys\" (just another form of ambulance chaser in my book) are just forcing bankruptcies upon people who would be willing to work a deal ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "and then they and the courts and the government are whining about what the bankruptcies do to the economy and the bottom line.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "fact", "text": "Last time I checked even in a court of law you can't play both sides.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "746", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "These are all excellent suggestions", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "but they don't address people who are incapable of paying down the interest bearing debt in a timely manner but could pay it down in a longer manner and if no more interest rate charges were accruing.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "765", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "A marital spouse is no longer a marital spouse when either martial partner dies.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "The end is death.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "A spouse doesn't remarry while still married,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "but unmarried people will remarry.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "A divorced spouse or a widowed spouse, may become the spouse of another once remarried.", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "The term spouse, in my opinion, relates to a marriage.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "fact", "text": "Once the marriage is over, the \"spouse\" is no longer a \"spouse.\"", "reasons": ["5"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "785", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "I think it should be kept uniform.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "It seems to make sense for sellers to send notification.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "239", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "First, I have learned there is a significant legal difference between 1) identify theft, 2) mistaken identity (see contract law", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "Furthermore, that these three words need to be separated, clarified and their legal handling completely examined.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "There is almost zero legal remedy for wrong person found.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "More information would NOT have helped.", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "The lawyer had plenty information ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "testimony", "text": "but he did not validate any of it after he found my address.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "testimony", "text": "The clerk told me these lawyers and their agents are \"just going through the phone book/internet\" hauling people with the same first and last name into court thinking they will eventually find the debtor.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "A complete waste of court resources, an enormous expense to the innocent citizen, and the unlawful detainment and threatening of an innocent citizen and their assets.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "testimony", "text": "The debtor, it has since been discovered has left the county.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "The lawyer could have easily validated his information using online public property records from both the Clerk of courts and the County Clerk and found out the middle initial was not a match along with over 7 other pieces of identifying information that were not a match.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "testimony", "text": "The lawyer did not even do the simplest checking.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "testimony", "text": "I filed with the IARDC ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "testimony", "text": "and nothing happened.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1212", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "It seems to me that the system must provide a series of 'handshakes': When a dispute is initiated; when the dispue is resolved; or when a dispute is withdrawn.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "In each case the consumer must know with certainty that the collector acknowledges the consumer's position and that the CRA has been properly notified.", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "The CRA must be party to the handshake,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "It is unacceptable that consumer's complaints can laguish for months with the consumer having no way to determine whether the CRA has received updated information from the collector or whether the CRA is taking unduly long to process the update.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1329", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I am saying that collection agencies cannot be trusted and more often than not go beyond their job scope.", "reasons": ["1", "2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "Some act as loan sharks and not collection agencies.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "I also think that their behavior is criminal when it comes to making threats against consumers and harassing people with disabilities and seniors.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "So, yes i think criminal charges should be pursued for their cover ups and harassment. Also other violations of privacy and fairness.", "reasons": ["1", "2"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "928", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I was just watching \"CBS This Morning\"", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "and they mentioned that FICO is going to be partnering with more financial institutions to allow the financial institutions\" customers to get their FICO score for free.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "FICO is already offered for free with many financial institutions,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "but now FICO is aggressively expanding this offer through their \"Open Access\" program.", "reasons": null, "evidence": ["4"]}, {"id": 4, "type": "reference", "text": "http://www.fico.com/en/Products/Scoring/Pages/FICO_Score_Open_Access.aspx", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have known about this ever since FICO put out a press release earlier this month.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "fact", "text": "What I found out today on \"CBS This Morning\" is that Discover is going to allow their cardholders to see their FICO score for free on their monthly billing statement.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "I don't think this is appropriate for Discover or any other business to put a consumer\"s FICO score on a billing statement or any other materials that can be turned over to debt collectors.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "fact", "text": "Right now, debt collectors do not have access to any consumers FICO score.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "fact", "text": "They do, however, have access to something called a \"collection score\"", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "value", "text": "which is nothing at all related to FICO or a consumers creditworthiness.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "value", "text": "This action by Discover is a HUGE privacy concern", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "policy", "text": "and the CFPB should not allow creditors or anyone else to have access to a consumer\"s FICO score.", "reasons": ["11"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1412", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "This Draft Summary of Discussion fails to address the issues of confusion about the statute of limitations and how they vary among states.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "This is a big source of confusion in terms of collection of a debt and jurisdiction.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "Creating a more stanadrized set of rules would alleviate these problems.", "reasons": ["3", "4", "6"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "In 2010, the FTC released a report, \"Repairing A Broken System,\" which made mention of the need a universal statute of limitations.", "reasons": null, "evidence": ["12"]}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "Additionally, in 2011 ACA's plan, \"The Path Forward: ACA International\"s Blueprint for Modernizing America\"s Consumer Debt Collection System\" also advocated for a national statute of limitations.", "reasons": null, "evidence": ["14"]}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "This is something that both sides of the industry actually agree upon.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "50 different states and 50 different statutes make it too confusing for consumers.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "I also reiterate that a compromise in terms of years can be reached.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "policy", "text": "Also, debt tolling needs to be done away with.", "reasons": ["9"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "It only adds to the confusion of when a debt becomes time-barred.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "value", "text": "We live in a transient society.", "reasons": ["11"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "policy", "text": "A debt should not legally follow a person for the rest of their life:", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "reference", "text": "Repairing A Broken System - Federal Trade Commission: http://www.ftc.gov/sites/default/files/documents/public_events/life-debt/debtcollectionreport_0.pdf", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 13, "type": "reference", "text": "InsideArm: Statutes of Limitations Frustrate Debt Collectors and Consumers http://www.insidearm.com/daily/debt-buying-topics/debt-buying/statutes-of-limitations-frustrate-debt-collectors-and-consumers", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 14, "type": "reference", "text": "The Path Forward: ACA International\"s Blueprint for Modernizing America\"s Consumer Debt Collection System: http://www.acainternational.org/files.aspx?p=/images/18898/finalblueprint-designedversion.pdf", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "864", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I do not have any debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "I was given a telephone number by Verizon that was previously owned by a person who had not paid her bills.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "Debt collectors have been calling me for 10 years now ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "and many have been threatening and intimidating.", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "One collector told me he had all my personal information and was going to ruin my life!!!", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "609", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "There's no need to be rude about it.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "There are some debt collection practices that should obviously be illegal.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "Other things that people are discussing here are obviously matters of convenience.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "To the extent that preferences are widely shared and outright prohibition wouldn't increase lending costs across the board beyond a marginal amount, outright prohibition makes sense.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "policy", "text": "But if someone wants the ability to stop someone from conducting any and all robocalls from all phones, and robocalls help creditors recoup their loans, then the creditor should be able to charge a regulated fee for that convenience.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "fact", "text": "I'm not saying that the debt collection agency itself would charge the fee", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "Just that a consent-based approach is another option.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "811", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "Email rules allows hiding emails and routing them in ways that surpass any other communication method.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "In addition, since email \"sender ID\" is easier to demand and maintain,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "debtors will have an easier time managing what communication they receive, and when.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "As a result, there is no necessity for forcing specific times of email delivery.", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "430", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "Unless the consumer chooses to communicate by phone, all correspondences from collectors should go through mail.", "reasons": ["1", "2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "This allows the consumer to take time in considering what the collector is requesting.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "It also avoids confusion for both parties.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "The only reason this isn't the standard approach is because it limits how annoying and embarrassing collectors can be--plain and simple.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "496", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I don't think that is the solution, ", "reasons": ["1", "2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "I hear there isn't room in the jails to put all the bill collectors.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "A lot of the multiple calls problems come from an dialer calling, if it doesn't get an answer it will call back later.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1217", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have never been deliquent on my State taxes.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "Due to an error made by the company I worked for in 2008, which didn't take out taxes, I am now faced with dealing with the State Collection agency.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "I have never heard of the State threating the residents to try to collect taxes.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "I called and coopertaed,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "however, the callers are harassing me from morning to night.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have excellent credit and have worked for many years to maintain my credit standing.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have never owed Federal taxes that I have not agreed to pay.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "testimony", "text": "And never in my life owed State taxes", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "and I am shocked that they can hound the residents like private collectors do.", "reasons": ["5", "6", "7"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "testimony", "text": "I am retired and and on a fixed income.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "value", "text": "For the State to be able to threaten the residents who are making attempts to pay the taxes, (one year) seems like a violation of rights.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "563", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "In my experience, simply contacting a person to collect a debt, time-barred or otherwise, implies litigation is possible and/or impending.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "It shoud be clearly stated in any communication if the debt is time-barred ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "and these types of debts should not be discussed by a phone call initiated by the collector.", "reasons": ["0"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1095", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "If our client(s) can't provide any verification of the debt, we close the account and send the debtor a letter that we are doing so.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "Note: this has only happened once or twice in 20 years.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "an unresolved dispute account should NOT be sold.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "If so, seller should be liable.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "371", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "If I have been falsely served or subserved, (the making up of a person who does not exist to claim a service, or simply stating \"Jane Doe\" received the service) and the judges don't care, and the debt collection companies don't care, I should have the right to file an errors and omissions insurance claim against the debt collection company for false service that resulted in a verdict against me.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have already tried asking for an errors and omissions insurance policy from the debt collection company ", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "so that I could file a claim and the debt collection company simply ignored my request.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "I find this both egregious and outrageous.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "363", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "If a make an offer to repay the creditor and it's refused, then the debt becomes time-barred, why should the creditor still be to sue?", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "If the creditor is offered a repayment plan, turns it down, then sues after an extended period of time, the consumer should not have to pay that debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1400", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "You are not living in the real world if you think it is just so easy, RBell.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "No, most consumers are not lawyers.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "The people using these debt collection practices are deliberately abusing the law ", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "because they know most who are harassed and in debt and working people who probably can't afford a lawyer.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "And I'll just bet it is worst in the states with the least amount of consumer protection.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "policy", "text": "Take care.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "You will sing a different tune when it is you on the meat hook.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "798", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Why are these questions putting the onus, once again, one the consumer?", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "It is the collectors who have harassed in the name of collecting a debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "It is pretty easy to distinguish landline from cellphone", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "google the number, that tells you.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "But creditors use recorded calling,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "policy", "text": "that should be stopped.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "If they have a well-trained person, that person ought to be able to determine the time zone the consumer lives in.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "I agree with the previous comment.", "reasons": ["8"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "policy", "text": "Creditors should assume the current mailing address is the correct one.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "How difficult is it to go from there in assessing the times that are appropriate to make calls?", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "783", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Well I do want to shout.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "You've never been on the receiving end of a collections company that treats people like cattle with dollar signs on them, whether they owe money or not.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "And it's been going on for years.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "Shame that is the first comment to make to me.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1159", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Not every debt collection agency is like that.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "The one I work for certainly isn't.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "240", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I had a particularly lousy experience with an abusive debt collector called Miracle Financial, working on behalf of Verizon Wireless to collect a debt I wasn't aware I had incurred and didn't believe I owed.", "reasons": ["3", "4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "The full account -- and dozens more from people leaving comments on my blog over the years -- is available at the supplied link.", "reasons": null, "evidence": ["2_4"]}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "I had my identity stolen", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "and I didn't even know it.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "They could not produce a signed credit card receipt to compare my signature.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "565", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "All creditors send out mutiple letters and make numerous phone calls to the consumer to give them a chance to pay their just incurred debt", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "and those letters will include the warning that the account will be turned over to a collection agency - not always SOLD to a collection agency, but they hire an agency to collect the debt on their behalf.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "And then the collection agency sends out multiple letters and makes calls.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "If the consumer feels this is not enough notice I am not sure what more can be done.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "policy", "text": "Consumers should talk to their creditors instead of ignoring the calls and letters and try to work out some kind of arrangement.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "But instead some do not want to take responisibility for their debt and try to push additional costs on the creditors because there were not enough letters sent out.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "It would be okay if the consumer wants more & more communications if the creditor or agency can bill the consumer for the postage.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "People wonder why the cost of health care and merchandise goes up", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "it is because consumers that do not pay their debts and requests laws that require the creditor to spend more and more time and money to try to collect", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1286", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "Right now collectors are legally required to stop phone contact when notified by the consumer.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "They do not stop.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "And the law is not enforced.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "Reporting violations to regulators does nothing except get the complainant into some sort of database, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "and the regulators are never heard from again.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "There are decent laws on the books.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "It's the enforcement that is a failure.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "655", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "If a debt is to be sold, the owner of the debt should be required to send an itemized statement to the debtor.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "The statement should have a large-type header, something like, \"[NAME OF CREDITOR] IS SELLING THIS DEBT TO [NAME OF DEBT BUYER].\"", "reasons": ["2", "3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "This would give the debtor another chance to pay in the simplest way, before getting tangled up in idiot phone calls, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "and it would help the debtor identify the debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1251", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "Collection email should not be sent to a consumers work place email address.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "As I stated earlier, email communication should be consumer initiated at this time unless the consumer specifically opts to list an email address of record with the 3 major credit reporting agencies.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "978", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "They didn't say a thing about it.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "They contacted him via phone ", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "since he was homeless at the time and told him they were taking him to court.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "They didn't even tell him which debt it was for initially.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "615", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "Require debt collectors to send validation notices via certified mail.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "There must be some way to prove the debt validation notice was at least sent, if not received.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have had the experience of a debt collector not sending me a validation notice.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "When I made a complaint to the Illinois Department of Professional Regulations, the debt collector did not have to prove that they sent the validation notice.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "All the debt collector had to do was claim that they had records of sending the validation notice in their computer system.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "testimony", "text": "Since I did not receive the validation notice, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "I did not know what my rights were.", "reasons": ["5"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "337", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "Debtors should be able to leave a message for a specific debtor, the name of their company and request a call-back at a specified number.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "When a consumer returns this type of call, the collector or debtor should be required to give them the mini-Miranda warning.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "There is no need for collectors to leave messages revealing the nature of their calls.", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "The Health Information Privacy and Portability Act prohibits disclosure of protected information to unauthorized parties", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "policy", "text": "and the same should apply to debt collectors.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "812", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Email isn't easier to access or view off the debtor's screen than a call", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "a call's content is actually harder to hide if you receive it among other people),", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "text message or SMS.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "The way regulation should handle sensitive information is by mandating that some information be an attachment, or in a link provided in the email, rather than the body of an email.", "reasons": ["4", "5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "If the attachment is encrypted or details are stored on a secured web page, no one will be able to access them.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "In fact, they will be much better protected than any other information relayed to the debtor.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "policy", "text": "Work emails should be handled differently, much like calls to a work place, which can also be accessed by the employer.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "528", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Texts will not work for consumers.", "reasons": ["1_2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "Consumers must pay for texts ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "and this is already against the law will rightly so.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "819", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Why can't we bring back the olden days?", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have been a \"victim\" of debt collectors run amok for over 35 years.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "Back in the day, a debt was assigned to one collector who would pursue me relentlessly for a debt that belonged to someone else.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "Nowadays with the robo-dialers the collection call is assigned to the \"next available operator.\"", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "Why not just go back to the days when only one collector was responsible for making the contact?", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1015", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "It sounds like you believe the creditor/debt collector's attorney should be responsible for giving legal advice to the consumer (i.e. the opposing party).", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "This is a serious conflict of interest and a violation of his duties to his client.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "Even worse, it sounds like you also want debt collectors who are NOT attorneys or employed by attorneys to also give legal advice to consumers.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "This is a violation of the prohibition on the unauthorized practice of law.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "I understand that the ignorance and lack of sophistication exhibited by defendant debtors is a concern.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "policy", "text": "I recommend that the CFPB develop a model notice of rights under the FDCPA.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "If it so chooses, it can also maintain on its website an area for state-specific resources related to State laws, and reference this website on the form notice.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "728", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "My experience is the collection agency will not correct the debt on the credit report!", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "we need a law requiring the collection company to report debt repayment or debt settlement to the credit bureau in a timely manner... Say 30 days after the debt has been settled, or payment arrangements have been made.", "reasons": ["0"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "It can be very hard to clean up your credit when working with collection companies...", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "they want their money but they don't care if your credit report is accurate!", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "360", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "Just like mortgage servicers are required to send \"goodbye letters\" (a notification of when loan has been sold) and \"hello letters\" (a notification of when another company is buying a debt), so also should debt collectors.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "Also, they should be required to disclose the amount for which they bought the debt... the discounted price.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "Also, there needs to be full disclosure as to who is buying the debt along with the disclosure of the owners of the debt collection company and the street address of the company", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "so face-to-face meetings can be arranged.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "policy", "text": "Full transparency and full disclosure should be required related to any company trying to collect debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "196", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "When alleged debtors are served with state court summonses, they are not always comprehensible to laypersons.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "Any requirements to file papers to avoid default judgment", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "The date of any scheduled hearing and procedures for changing the date", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "Local and online sources of information for pro se defendants, and possibly local non-profit advice organizations.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "policy", "text": "That the debtor may wish to consider bankruptcy if they cannot pay their debts.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "751", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Larry S, your quote...\"A plaintiff in a lawsuit cannot be placed in a situation where it is rewarding to sue with insufficient cause and minimal risk\" is a very powerful statement and one that I entirely agree with.", "reasons": ["1", "2_3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "It is this scenario that emboldens debt collectors to hire riff raff service companies who will lie about doing a legal service or sub service, and apparently get away with it.", "reasons": null, "evidence": ["2"]}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have been victimized by two false subservices.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "I think both were done by the same service company.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1350", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "A certified letter plus a regular letter should be sent.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "It proves that a consumer is at least aware of the debt and has X time to respond.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "Should cost any more then the postage of the regular letter.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "531", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "Actually a dialer does not call back.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "Your dialer has been purposely setup that way by YOUR IT dept.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "I bet you would lose in the knowledge of dialers.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "716", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "When the first collection agency can't collect they sell the debt to 2nd tier collectors.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "They sometimes sell it to 3rd tier collectors.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "My experience in helping resolve collection disputes is sometimes the first collector and always the third collectors do not provide debt validation letters.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "342", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "Consumers should not incur additional costs for cell phone calls, texting or voice messaging in relation to collections.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "The more costs assessed to a debtor, the less money they have to pay their creditors.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "Debt collectors and creditors should be required to stop all modes of communication to a device that the debtor indicates does not provide free communications whether calls or texts.", "reasons": ["0"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1152", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "This is an awesome suggestion!", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "Your suggestion \"I don't think they should be allowed to call ANY number for more than 3 months without successful contact with the debtor\" is spot on!", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "And I can't believe that no one else has ever suggested this before.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "3 months (or whatever an appropriate time limit is) would reduce the constant harassment that I and many other innocent parties receive.", "reasons": ["4_7"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "This morning I received an illegal phone call from a collector at 6:17 AM with a spoofed phone number for a person that I have never known", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "testimony", "text": "and I have told these collectors this several times already.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "testimony", "text": "They have the wrong number.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "And I am tired of this.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "policy", "text": "The CFPB should absolutely implement a rule that forces unsuccessful contact to 3 months.", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "689", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I believe that this practice in already in place in three major ways.", "reasons": ["1", "2", "3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "The creditor usually already requires all of their customers to provided updated contact information,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "Once a consumer moves the address change and other contact information changes are updated on the consumers credit report,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "and finally, The USPS has records of mail forwarding procedures once a consumer moves.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "695", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "You are correct.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "There is quite a difference between send and receive.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "All I am suggesting is that a creditor only be required to send any notice to the last known address - not that the consumer receive it.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "and you presume too much if you think that all mail is returned if not delivered to the proper recipeint),", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "policy", "text": "then the creditor must send the notice to that new address.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "policy", "text": "If the point of this dialogue is to ensure the consumer is protected, then require the consumer to protect themselves and provide this information to the creditor.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "If they don't then a creditor can't be hanged in a lawsuit for a letter failing to reach a consumer, when the creditor actions used the best information on hand.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1339", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "I think the cost of education needs to be reduced to a more reasonable amount or repayment plans need to be income based.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "As far as consumer protection, legal aid needs to be made available, affordable and effective,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "and consumers need to take time to really know their rights and stop complaining about harassment", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "because that's a completely different cause of action than restitution.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1388", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I appreciate Mr. Bartmann's comments", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "but they appear to be grounded in a collection agency perspective ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "(there is always business and market share tension between collection agencies and law firms).", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "The reality is that (and this was voiced by other participants) many (not all but many) debtors simply won't/can't pay until they have to.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "The FDCPA and TCPA have truly made communications with debtor both difficult and hazardous for the collector.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "For instance, the fact that you can't safely leave a voice message for a debtor should be very troubling.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "testimony", "text": "Over the years, our firm has stopped initial outbound calling (responding only to inbound calls) and also limited our pre-suit letters to just two.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "testimony", "text": "We send the required disclosure letter and (there being no response and the account reviewed for suit) then send a discounted payment offer that says we are going to file suit but would rather settle.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "testimony", "text": "We offer reasonable terms to the debtors to avoid a costly suit but ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "the response rate is absolutely miserable, probably in the single digits percentage wise.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "value", "text": "Believe me, suits are time consuming and expensive, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "fact", "text": "but they are often simply the only option.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "testimony", "text": "Even when the debtors are served, few contact us, and even fewer when the court sends them the judgment.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 13, "type": "value", "text": "Worse, a judgment doesn't guarantee payment on the account.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 14, "type": "value", "text": "Clarification via Regulations as to what we can say and do in communications would at least promote more communication between the parties.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 15, "type": "value", "text": "With that, perhaps more points of contact could resolve debts before suit.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 16, "type": "value", "text": "I strongly disagree that litigation should be \"discouraged\"", "reasons": ["17"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 17, "type": "value", "text": "as it is not only a simple reality in much of debt collection but a fundamental right of a creditor.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 18, "type": "value", "text": "However, I think Regulations making it clear what can and cannot be done in communications that can shield the industry from the wild west of FDCPA and TCPA lawsuits would greatly encourage more communication.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 19, "type": "value", "text": "I also think a reasonable, good faith attempt to resolve the case (offering a payment plan and/or lump sum) before suit is filed is still a good idea as well ", "reasons": ["21"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 20, "type": "value", "text": "even though our own response rate has not been great.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 21, "type": "value", "text": "Anything more will infringe on a creditor's rights and interfere with state law.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 22, "type": "value", "text": "Perhaps the CFPB Portal could have a debt resolution aspect to it where a debtor could try to resolve an account in a \"safer\" more disarming manner.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "581", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "Old debt that is beyond the statue of limitation should indicate the original creditor in the initial contact letter.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "I think the collector does not know this information or they deliberately refuse to disclose it because they know that the debt has run it course through the CRA's for seven years.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "So why is it that a collector can rename themselves as the merchant because they bought an old debt and proceed to collect and to report it to the CRA's.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "Once your credit has taken a hit the debt collector should not be able to continually harass you for the rest of your existence.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "Portfolio Recovery is the culprit ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "policy", "text": "and they should not be able to look at your credit report and send letters to collect as if you entered into a legal and binding contract with them.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "Why should you reactivate an old debt that is over 16 years old.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "fact", "text": "Everyone know and remember the hard patches in their lives, such as medical issues, divorces, death etc.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "Once the fear of being sued is removed, the chances of a collector to collect is very minute.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "So it becomes time consuming and it cost money to send a certified letter to ask them to validate an alleged debt.", "reasons": ["8"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "policy", "text": "If the collector can not validate a debt then they should not continually sell and resell such debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "value", "text": "And there is a problem with the CRA's ", "reasons": ["12"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "value", "text": "because it seems to me they are in cahoots with each other.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 13, "type": "policy", "text": "If there si not any active business with a particular account on a credit report, then the CRA's should make the collector prove that a debt is valid.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "379", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "As a mortgage lender for an FDIC-insured bank, I'm astounded at the number of customers who sit across from me and are wholly dumbfounded when I tell them their loan request is denied because of outstanding collections.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "For certain there are some people who knew full well they would have collections items and are playing dumb (and not doing so very well).", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "But many of them had no clue,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "and 90% of those collections are medical in nature.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "policy", "text": "If the CFPB truly is about protecting the interests of the consumer, then the debt collection process needs to be simplified drastically in regard to collection items (medical, utilities, etc.).", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "after 60 days of non-payment, the account can be closed.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "The creditor sends a certified letter to the last known address of the debtor, informing them they have 30 days to bring the account current or make other payment arrangements, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "or the account will be turned over to a collection agency.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "policy", "text": "Said letter also needs to contain the contact information for that collection agency,", "reasons": ["9"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "so they know in advance who to contact if they don't respond within 30 days.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "value", "text": "Yes, a lot of those letters will be returned undeliverable or will end up in someone else's hands.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "value", "text": "But that would demonstrate a good faith effort by the creditors to work with the debtors before passing the buck to a collection agency.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "value", "text": "The added benefit for the government is the increase in certified letters passing through the USPS!", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1020", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "But private arrangement between these entities doesn't change the fact that the money is still owed.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "Just because the original creditor took a loss on it, doesn't change what is really due.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "Is it ethical for someone to rack up tens of thousands of dollars of debt and never pay it back?", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1016", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I think the Massachusetts rule is a positive step in the right direction, and would be better than the current situation.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "However, for those debtors who truly cannot pay at all, due to a serious adverse life event, such as the loss of a job due to a medical disability, their situation is not likely to change from week to week.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "For example, most disability insurance companies only require a patient's doctor to submit a re-certification of the patient's medical disability every 3, 6, or 12 months.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "In essence, the debt collector would be acting as a sort of medical re-certification investigator twice a week, which is unnecessary, burdensome on both debtor and collector, and potentially harassing.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "351", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I believe the original consumer applicant on an account has the right to know if an authorized user is delinquent on her or his payments", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "as it affects the original applicant's credit standing.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "As for telling authorized card holders about the original account holder's default, I would say this is not a good idea.", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "Many parents provide their kids with a credit card, but would not want the credit card company contacting their kids about the parents' debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "554", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Potential for abuse.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "Here comes your neighbor knocking telling you he's getting calls looking for you.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "The same with family members makes holiday gatherings fun since it's clear it's a debt collector doing some location acquisition.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "428", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Calling someone's work is clearly and without dispute intended to embarrass and annoy.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "It is never acceptable.", "reasons": ["0"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "321", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "Debt collectors should not be permitted to harass a debtor's ex-spouse by repeatedly calling the ex-spouse.", "reasons": ["1_3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "Debt collectors are known to use the old phone number of the debtor that now belongs to the ex-spouse exclusively.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "Even though the ex-spouse tells the collector to remove her phone number from the collector's records, the collector does not,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "and then repeatedly calls her trying to get to the debtor.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "policy", "text": "Collectors must be required to remove her phone number from their records at her first request and not be permitted to call her again.", "reasons": ["0", "5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "Otherwise, she has no recourse to get the harassment to stop.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "352", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "Consumer owing the debt should be contacted about any third party offer to pay their debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "Anyone paying debt for someone else should be required to provide their identity to the creditor and debtor.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "524", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "I think that both an English and Spanish letter should be sent.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "This already happens with most legal and other important things (like voting and letters from school) in my State.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "But this should be a fed requirement to always include Spanish.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "747", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "and if you remain skeptical, please check out this article by a completely independent source about global debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "reference", "text": "<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://seekingalpha.com/article/1832102-global-debt-elephant-in-the-room?source=google_news\"> Global Debt Elephant in the Room.</a>", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "486", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "No phone calls at work.", "reasons": ["2", "3_4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "I agree!", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "Work is for work, not personal debt business.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "I personally don't get calls at work,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "but I can see how embarrassing it would be and how quickly the company would probably fire.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "policy", "text": "No work phone calls period, should be the law.", "reasons": ["2", "3_4"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "434", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I had one debt collector in particular who called me a liar when I told him I wasn't the person he was looking for.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "This was after he violated the FDCPA by calling me at 7:00 on a Saturday morning.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "I called them back immediately and spoke with a supervisor who said she'd take me off their hit list.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "I asked her if she got my number out of the phone book.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "She claimed that they had not.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "testimony", "text": "A few months later, they started in on me again.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "Obviously they still considered me a liar.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "testimony", "text": "I sent them a cease-communication letter with a copy to my state's Attorney General, who has been wonderful in all this.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "testimony", "text": "At that point, I started sending out letters every time I received a collection call, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "testimony", "text": "and, other than the one, none ever called me again.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "testimony", "text": "At one point I was receiving daily calls from one collector or another.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "testimony", "text": "I can name names, and I have a thick file folder full of copies of my letters and responses to my Attorney General.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "value", "text": "It has been a wild ride, and I sure hope it's over.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 13, "type": "testimony", "text": "I'm approaching the one-year anniversary of my most recent collection call.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 14, "type": "value", "text": "I just wish they wouldn't use the phone book as their primary research tool.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1337", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "This question is most interesting with respect to student loans.", "reasons": ["2", "3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "Unlike most other debts, student loans have the potential to be greater than $75k, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "which means a consumer can be sued in Federal Court under supplemental jurisdiction provisions.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "Additionally, should the current creditor be able to achieve complete diversity, the consumer can be sued in an entirely different state.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "602", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "They could set transparent, limited rate increases which debt collectors could charge for each mode of communication that is eliminated.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "A rule setting that kind of rate increase would add some necessary transparency to the question of whether these kinds of communications are even worthwhile for the agency.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "758", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "For attorney debt collectors, being required to provide a list of all the rights the consumer may have comes perilously close to the provision of legal advice;", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "even if it doesn't cross that line, the unsophisticated debtor may believe that an attorney is acting as a neutral court officer rather than as an advocate for an adverse party.", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "I've had debtors ask me \"Do I need to come to court for this?\" after I've sued them.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "621", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "They could at least start with address and area code of debtor\"s phone number.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "And I would say that the reach would be at least as far as the local commuting area.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "So for a city like Boston, there's Boston, Chelsea, and the other surrounding areas.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "Now, if a debtor from NY traveled to Boston for the marathon, for example, that would be much harder for a collector to have a reasonable expectation of a debtor\"s whereabouts.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "policy", "text": "But once a debtor has identified his/herself within the reach of the commuting area of the place of emergency, then perhaps the exemption period should kick in.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "policy", "text": "In a place like Newtown, or Colorado, if a collector has a reasonable belief that a debtor may have been an employee of the school or movie theater (if they can't identify the debtor being in the local commuting area by address/phone number), then they should also stop collection for the exemption period.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "So, place of employment, address, phone number, and debtors self-identifying their whereabouts, could be ways that debt collectors could/should have reason to believe the location of a debtor.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1122", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "This is not an appropriate requirement", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "because not all states have licensing or registration for debt collectors.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "435", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "Legally, I don't believe that CFPB authority should stretch into this area ", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "since the federal laws do not include such a limitation.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "Notification to a consumer that a debt is beyond statute is problematic", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "since that date is not permanent.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "Partial payment on an account restarts the statute of limitations.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "I don't believe that a rule issued by the CFPB can help here.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "Education of consumers is the only pro-active method that I see as available here.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "policy", "text": "However, this education should include notification to the legal profession that the CFPB will bring violations in this area to the attention of the Attorney General in their state.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "559", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Many recommendations are dispute credit report in writing ", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "since online is more rushed by the people hired to handle this.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "No requirement to do it online.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "200", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "Consumer attorneys occasionally advise their clients not to record unlawful communications due to state laws requiring both parties' consent for recording.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "The CFPB should require that debt collectors subject to the FDCPA impliedly consent to recording by consumers.", "reasons": ["0"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "740", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I would suggest that debtors who INVOLUNTARILY defaulted on a debt don't have the money to hire an attorney,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "so they don't see the point to going to court without an attorney.", "reasons": ["0"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "Why doesn't the court give access to free legal counsel to debt defaulters the way they do to those who are accused of committing a crime?", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "863", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "We have no debt other than what is current on our credit cards, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "but for 10 or15 years we have been receiving robo calls for an Edward Flanigan.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "We've owned this number for 22 years and have never known an Edward Flanigan.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "We are on the do not call list.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "policy", "text": "Robo calls by debt collectors need to be banned outright.", "reasons": ["0_2"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1120", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Information about the source of the debt (such as the date of the service) can be provided without infringing on the patient's privacy.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "No one should be asked to pay a debt without first being told why they owe the money.", "reasons": ["0"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "This is esp. true of medical debts, ", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "which are notoriously complex and apparently redundant, with many charges occurring on the same occasion.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "676", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Tiffany, I think part of the problem is that the 2% of collectors who harass and abuse are responsible for a disproportionate share of the contacts that consumers have with your industry.", "reasons": ["1_3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "Everyone (whether they owe a debt or not) has had an encounter with one of these bad apples,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "and then they want to take out their anger on you.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "And when you make an honest mistake and get sued for a technical violation, you pay the same penalty as a company that has deliberately harassed someone with 100 phone calls.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "456", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Yes, one of the biggest scams that consumers get put through is the collection agency saying discussions about the debt have to be made with the parent company,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "and the parent company saying they cannot talk about the debt because it has been assigned to a debt collection agency,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "Please FIX THIS.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1030", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Preserving the industry DOES protect consumers.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "If there isn't a lawful and enforceable way of collecting money that is owed, then future consumers will pay the price in increased cost for credit, or denial of credit entirely due to risk.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "429", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I don't know what constitutes as \"repeatedly or continuously,\"", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "but more than once a day seems to qualify.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "The system is designed to give collectors complete control, leaving the consumer with none.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "Letters through the mail is a much more effective approach,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "but collectors refuse to honor that request.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "705", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "this is not necessarily true.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "There are services that text and the sender pays for the text.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1371", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I believe that a universal statute of limitations would be an effective way to end debt tolling.", "reasons": ["1", "2", "3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "If there was a universal statute of limitations, there would be no need for debt tolling.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "Collectors would be able to file suit no matter where the debtor lived based on a single set of federal laws.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "It also makes things less confusing for debtors ", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "(they know that they can be sued within X amount of years no matter where they go, hence they can't \"run\" from debt", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "and debt collectors don't have to go from state to state, wading through murky laws.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "policy", "text": "Furthermore, debt collectors should not have the privilege of hiding behind tolling laws.", "reasons": ["8"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "policy", "text": "Either they sue or they don't within a federally mandated set of time.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "Tolling simply keeps zombie debt going and going.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "315", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have been contacted about a collection agency that stated that an old prescription charge was unpaid.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "The total was like $1500.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "When I asked for proof, I received a piece of paper that had three numbers on it that added up to $1500.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "Nothing more.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "Literally.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "policy", "text": "When a consumer asks for proof, they should at the very least receive a fully itemized listing of what it is is being collecting upon. (e.g. a detailed statement of account, or the un-paid invoice(s).", "reasons": ["0_4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "policy", "text": "Additionally, consumers should receive documentation as to why they are legally responsible. (E.g. an agreement that they signed.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "I realize that for businesses that traffic in unpaid consumer debt this is going to be a huge burden ", "reasons": ["8"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "as this information has long been lost.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "Too bad.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "policy", "text": "At the very least, this should be the standard for any debts incurred after a certain date.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "398", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "\"Verify\" needs to be thoroughly defined.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "It should be no less than documented court admissible evidence that the consumer is responsible for the debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "If the debt collector cannot produce this evidence, he should be barred from reselling the debt or reporting it to the CRAs.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "967", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "This so-called \"validation notice\" might better be called a 'justification notice.'", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "After all, the notification should supply the justification underlying the demand for payment; (\"Why am I being asked to pay this money?\").", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "This justification, obviously, should clearly specify the original transaction; i.e., specific product or service purchased, prior efforts to collect, (the history of the collection efforts) and present status.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "It's not so much 'additional information' which is required,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "it's more the clarity of the information provided.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "policy", "text": "That said, I'm convinced that communications between creditor and debtor should avoid words like 'creditor' and 'debtor,' along with words like, 'charge-off', 'default' (already mentioned by myself and emmacollector in this thread) and any and all words that belong in an accounting 101 book.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "I understand what these words signify ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "and sometimes I get confused by who's the creditor and who's the debtor.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "policy", "text": "Again, simplicity, which entails clarity, ought to be the guiding principle.", "reasons": ["7"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "338", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Calling a debtor at work is counter-intuitive;", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "if collectors are continuously calling someone at work, other employees may report it to the debtor's supervisor.", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "Most companies have established rules about receiving or making personal calls from company or cell phones during an employee's working hours.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "If a collector or creditor calls a debtor on his/her cell phone and is informed that the debtor is at work, the call should be terminated.", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "policy", "text": "No calls to employers should be allowed ", "reasons": ["5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "as this jeopardizes the debtor's job.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "How does that help in debt collection? It doesn't.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "755", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Jeffreyjon, it sounds like you are identifying how a strategic defaulter acts.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "However, Involuntary Defaulters don't have the income available to pay down a debt if the interest rate charges are going to keep accruing.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "543", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "Make the authorized user pay.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "It is so dumb when I tell these collectors \"call my brother he charged it\" and they say \"I cant you are the account holder hes just an authorized user.\"", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "Seriously?!", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "So old fashioned.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1201", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "In Michigan a company had its Collection Agency Revoked due to unethical practices 2008.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "But this did not stop them.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "Now they practice as attorneys and continue the unethical practices.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "Yes states must figure out how to close this loophole.", "reasons": ["0_2"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1194", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I was a reference for an ex-boyfriend on a student loan application.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "One of the FDCPA rules is that the reference can only be contacted once by a creditor.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "Well, each time the account is sold to a new collection agency, they call me again,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "even though I tell them I have no idea where he is.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "I think creditors skirt the FDCPA regulations in a manner that harasses consumers.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "policy", "text": "For any given account, the reference should only be able to be called a set amount of times--such as the first three collection agencies to purchase the debt from the original creditor.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "testimony", "text": "Here it is, almost 9 years later, and I am still getting calls for a person who is now a stranger to me.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "testimony", "text": "Since it is a student loan,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "it could go on forever.", "reasons": ["7", "9"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "fact", "text": "There is no statute of limitations for government guraranteed debt that I am aware of...", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "228", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "There should be no option to attempt to verify the debt.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "Attempts should always be required", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "and if verification is not made, the debt cannot be further transferred.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "881", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "As someone who has dealt for over two years with a rogue collections company putting a debt I don't owe on my credit report, I think these debt buyers should be disallowed by law.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "Legitimate third parties can operate,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "but these fly by night businesses who buy for pennies on the dollar without a care as to whether the books are correct should be fined and put out of business.", "reasons": ["0"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "In other words, the regulations should be so tough that they can't afford to stay open.", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "They only wreak havoc on people.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have dealt with an unscrupulous company for two years;", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "testimony", "text": "my state Attorney General was involved in getting it removed from my credit report with 1 agency, only to have this company report the same to another agency.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "policy", "text": "No collection should be allowed on the credit report until verified 100%.", "reasons": ["5_6"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "policy", "text": "And if the debt is more than 2 years old, the creditor must notify the supposed debtor in writing and allow 30 days for a response--denial, request for proof, payment, etc.--before putting it on the credit report.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "955", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "They need to include the name of the original creditor as well as the account number and the brand name the consumer would recognize. Date and amount of last payment, copy of the last billing statement (supposedly) sent to the consumer.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "However I also think they need to send a copy of the original debt document with the consumer's signature.", "reasons": ["2_3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "Someone can send me bills for something I don't owe,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "but they can't send me a signed paper I never signed.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1006", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "Additionally, collectors should not be allow, under ANY circumstance, to use any method which would cost the conusmer money.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "For example, cellphones and texting should be banned completely from calls from collectors.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "947", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "If you have a standing complaint with a company's mishandling of your account and/or complaints with any federally recognized oversight bureau, like CFPB, a company should be required to resolve the dispute before prosecuting what they define as a breach of debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "Banks and companies should not be allowed to try to prosecute over \"missed\" payments that were erroneously processed by them.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "Especially when evidence has been provided to the contrary and disputes are on file.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "Continuing to place the burden of proof on the consumer is onerous and prohibitive for many consumers.", "reasons": ["4_5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "I personally had a problem with a mortgage company", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "and the amount of my time it took to get the problem resolved was worth 20% of the original principal amount.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "policy", "text": "If a consumer complaint is on file, the company should be burdened with disproving the consumer complaint before prosecuting.", "reasons": ["7"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "They have both the financial and personnel resources to do so, whereas a consumer usually does not.", "reasons": ["8"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "Otherwise, why wouldn't they continue to bully and defraud consumers to boost bottom line profits?", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1114", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I would like to see strict regulation of the so-called \"skip-trace\" vendors.", "reasons": ["2", "3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "These are the companies that debt collectors and others hire to provide them with contact information.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "From my own personal experience (common last name, many debt collectors after me), I can say that I believe that I'm at the mercy of these vendors.", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "They gather all sorts of information about people without verifying any of it, as far as I can tell.", "reasons": null, "evidence": ["4_6"]}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "One debt collector told my state's Attorney General that they hired one of these vendors who provided my phone number as a valid contact for someone with my last name and first initial.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "This person was a stranger to me,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "but the debt collector wanted me to pay the debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "policy", "text": "I think that these vendors should be strictly regulated and use a research tool other then the phone book to gather their information.", "reasons": ["2", "8"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "policy", "text": "They should not be able to provide \"valid\" information unless it really is valid.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "402", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I was never informed by Bank of America that they sold my credit card and closed the card.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "When I realized it, I paid it off immediately.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "During that quarter, after long illnesses, my Father and Mother both passed (within 31 days of each other) ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "and frankly, credit card payments were not in the forefront of my thinking.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "ALSO, just because a bank or credit card company has been exempted from Usury laws does not mean they do not commit the violation!", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "policy", "text": "THAT needs to be stopped!", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "369", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have personally witnessed how judges perceive credit card debt cases,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "and I believe they have strayed too far towards the debt collectors.", "reasons": ["2_3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "Judges simply decide whether a default has occurred,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "and once a judge declares a debtor in default, the adjudicated debtor has no pleading rights.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "policy", "text": "Alleged credit card and student loan defaulters should have the right to declare their default an Involuntary Default and be allowed to pay back the debt with no more penalties, fees or interest rate charges, called Debt Neutrality.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "fact", "text": "Debt Neutrality is making of a debt neutral so that it does not continue to indenture a defaulter in a never ending cycle of ongoing interest rate charges, penalties and fees.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "policy", "text": "Involuntary defaults should allow the debtor to have the debt reset to where it was at the time of the default minus any payments made.", "reasons": ["7"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "As it stands now, Strategic Defaulters are given much better treatment than Involuntary Defaulters,", "reasons": ["8"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "in large part due to Involuntary Defaulters not being able to plead their default as being Involuntary.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "333", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "A debt collector did not litigate a credit card debt, but summarily garnished our joint checking account.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "It was two weeks later that notification was received from the debt collector.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "This occurred September-October 2012.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "Debt Collectors must provide advance notice of their intent to garnish a checking account.", "reasons": ["0_2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "It took several weeks including an Order from the Judge to release the funds, only after the Debt Collector took all of a tax refund.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1090", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "We instruct our collectors to treat EVERY dispute the same--whether received in writing or over the phone and without regard to when it was received.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "Therefore, I agree that debtors should provide the information referenced in FCRA.", "reasons": ["0"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "The problem with FCRA disputes is the E-Oscar system that only affords the collector a couple options like \"account information is accurate as of date reported\"\"", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "this doesn't even make sense as a response to the info provided by the debtor.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "policy", "text": "If E-Oscar is going to be a valid \"dispute\" under FDCPA, that website needs some serious updating including making sure that disputes actually contain the information listed in CFR 1022.43(d) and allowing collectors to transmit the actual contract/itemized statements/etc back to the debtor.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1181", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "Although I don't think that it is necessary for the CFPB to have undercover agents, I do think that the CFPB should create a new class of examiners.", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "Currently the CFPB examiners only do examinations of the financial lenders and nonbank lenders.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "But since the CFPB is now taking on the collection industry,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "the CFPB should create a new classification of examiners to do onsite examinations of the debt collection companies.", "reasons": ["2", "4", "5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "This would not create any harm to the CFPB ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "nor would it impact the CFPB\"s budget or operations.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "fact", "text": "The CFPB\"s budget is not allocated through congressional legislation \"", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "fact", "text": "it is allocated through monetary transfers from the Federal Reserve.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "All the CFPB would need to do is ask for additional transfers from the Federal Reserve to create this new classification of examiners.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "These new examiners would help the CFPB monitor the debt collection industry and would help stimulate the economy by adding more jobs.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "value", "text": "This is a win-win solution.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1347", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "False of misleading are rearranging paper work to suit their claims, false allegations against the lender, personal harassment, humiliation on credit reports, preventing students from seeking consolidation form other companies.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "Other false or misleading is the assumption that students dont want to repay their loans.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "That is not true.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "They also mix up the paper work so much it is difficult to get to the bottom of why the loans are in default in the first place.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "policy", "text": "They need to streamline their services and offer students option in the private loan sector.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "policy", "text": "The institutions should do the same", "reasons": ["6"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "because they treat student loans like mortgage loans.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1284", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "It doesn't just \"occasionally\" happen.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "It happens all the time.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "Those of us with common names are sitting ducks for these scumbags.", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "I am constantly harassed by collectors looking for someone else.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "Call blocking programs do not work out of area, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "so call-blocking is no protection whatever.", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1263", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I believe reasonable will depend on the circumstance of the dispute and the type of debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "A formal checklist should be created for various scenarios ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "and the analyst reviewing the dispute should be able to enter comments against the checklist which would be part of the eoscar transcript.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1093", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "The CFPB should clarify whether \"verify\" means verify that you are a legitimate collection agency (not a scam) OR does it mean to prove the legitimacy of the account relative to the debtor's objections.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "If is the former, some basic information relative to the account--contract, itemized statements, or any other identifying information that only the creditor would have access to would suffice.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "If CFPB wants \"verify\" to answer every single objection a debtor can cook up, a collector could never move forward without spending hundreds of hours normally reserved for litigation.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "As to a time frame on answering, I think the current system of stopping collection action until verification is provided is appropriate.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "Normally, sending the information to the debtor is not the hard part.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "Getting the info from the creditor and then circling back around to this particular account is what takes the time.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "policy", "text": "I don't think disputes should be limited to the first 30 days, but should be prohibited once suit has been filed.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "The Court rules and discovery process provide the debtor all the access to this information they could ever need or want", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "and the provide this access under pretty strict penalties from the Court if the creditor/plaintiff does not provide the info requested.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "810", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Email communication is a huge advantage for all involved parties.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "Emails provide consumers with much better tools to control how they are being contacted.", "reasons": ["12", "2", "3", "5", "8", "9"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "First, if treating emails as \"in writing\" (as they should), disputing a debt or demanding that collectors cease communication is much easier.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "Second, setting rules to hide collection notices is a powerful tool not available in any other communication medium.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "3rd party disclosure is therefore a lesser concern.", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "Third, email delivery is fast, and facilitates an efficient process, where less communications can be made to reach a settlement.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "fact", "text": "Everything is in writing.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "Fourth, email is significantly less confrontational than phone calls ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "and causes much less stress to recipients.", "reasons": ["7"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "Fifth, email is better than recording in keeping record of communication,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "value", "text": "making it even harder for collectors to hide acts of non compliance.", "reasons": ["9"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "policy", "text": "Email should be allowed, while keeping the sensitive parts of the message (disclosures, personal details etc) hidden - as an attachment or as a link that is part of an email.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "value", "text": "Yes, email is more cost efficient to collectors", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 13, "type": "policy", "text": "which is why using email should be conditional on collectors not charging the debtors any fees for their payments.", "reasons": ["12"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 14, "type": "policy", "text": "The added profitability should be shares with the consumer.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1349", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Too many collectors call and never report the \"mini-Miranda warning\".", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "They call all times of the day and night, and multiple times of the day.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "If they don't get you because your have called ID, they will change their ID and try again.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "It is simply harrassment.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "Many will challenge the the consumer, threaten, and even harrass them to the point that I saw someone actually contemplate suicide.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "policy", "text": "Also, when a debt is sold, the information for the orginal details need to go with it.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "fact", "text": "many times these collectors will call, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "fact", "text": "and they have no details on debts that are 5 and 6 years old, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "fact", "text": "and the consumer doesn't rememer it.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "219", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Maybe I missed something", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "but I never received any notice from my original mortgage lender that my mortgage was sold.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "Maybe that is better", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "since the new \"owner\" may be a pool of investors.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "my experience was the buyer sent the notice listing the original creditor name.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "Requiring the seller and buyer to send a notice would cause consumer confusion.", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1101", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I'm not sure a registration system for debt collectors really addresses the issue.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "I'm not exactly sure how the registration system would operate.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "In MA, consumers can check online to see whether a debt collector is licensed to practice in the state,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "many just don't know about the website or on a more basic level don't know that the debt collector has no right to try to collect from them.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "Is the registration system meant to displace state laws requiring licensing of debt collectors in the individual states?", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "I hope that's not the case", "reasons": ["6"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "since states have a strong interest in regulating debt collectors for the protection of its consumers.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "889", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have been a frequent target of debt collectors and their phone calls for several years.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "The reason, clearly, is because I have a common last name.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "I do not have any debts.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "First, once a debt collector starts calling me, it is extremely difficult to get rid of them.", "reasons": ["4", "5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "One outfit called me a liar and kept calling.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "testimony", "text": "Another went after me for two different people.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "Second, yes, a barrage of collection calls can be harmful.", "reasons": ["7", "9"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "Dealing with debt collectors on a daily basis has taken its toll on my physical and mental health.", "reasons": ["8"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "testimony", "text": "I'm an old lady.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "It has also made me paranoid about my own finances.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "677", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "I do not believe that use of social media should be allowed to initiate or to conduct any legal or other sensitive arrangements or communications to and from debt collectors.", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "There are a couple of things that I've noticed about social media:", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "social media is a fad, and an outlet.", "reasons": ["3", "4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "People use social media as an outlet for the narcissistic/public/storybook/memorable moments side of their lives.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "And recent evidence shows that fewer teens and young adults are using facebook and twitter.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "And I am most certain that no social media user would like for their private life to become public life by dealing with a debt collector on facebook.", "reasons": ["6"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "Nobody likes to be in debt and have bill collectors chasing them,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "In writing\" to me, means a letter delivered in the mail.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "I would also accept an interpretation to mean delivered by email but only on official company letterhead documents. And only if first requested by the debtor and not first initiated by the collector.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "But I can not accept \"in writing\" to mean messages and communication sent via social media.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "policy", "text": "I think that E-Sign consent should only be valid for the original creditor.", "reasons": ["12_13"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "policy", "text": "And any and every collector who then gets involved must get the debtor to consent E-Sign with them.", "reasons": ["10"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "value", "text": "The reason is because there are some things that I, as a consumer, am comfortable with dealing online or through email with my original creditors,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 13, "type": "value", "text": "but there are things that I know I would not feel comfortable dealing with online/email with a debt collector.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 14, "type": "policy", "text": "So E-Sign should not be blanket consent for anyone and everyone.", "reasons": ["12_13"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1029", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "When debt collectors send that Validation Notice, they are required to state the creditor to whom the debt is owed.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "I think that is sufficient notice that the debt is being assigned for collection.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "I commented on the other thread that I DO believe notice should be given when the debt is sold.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "But if the current creditor is retaining ownership but just assigning it to a collection agency or law firm, they will be notified when that agency contacts them and sends a Validation Notice.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "Besides, the collection agency or law firm may end up refusing to accept the account due to a conflict or a variety of other reasons.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "Giving notice that ends up being false would certainly cause confusion.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "370", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Debt Collection companies get a very unfair debt negotiation advantage against an alleged defaulter when they hire an unscrupulous service company that has lied about giving a proper service or subservice to the alleged debtor's residence.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "Judges do not seem to understand that if a service company will fraudulently state in court documents that they served a defaulter or subserved someone at the residence when in fact they did not, that the debt collector can become very arrogant and cocky as to how they negotiate with the alleged defaulter.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "In a nutshell, if the debt collector's one sided terms are not met, they will simply hire the service company who will provide service even if it is a false service.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "Judges rationalize that the mail service is an adequate notification without realizing that what a false service does is embolden the debt collection company to not properly negotiate a debt with an alleged defaulter because they have total control over the service aspect, even if fraudulently obtained.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "policy", "text": "This need to be fixed", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "policy", "text": "and false servers need to be fined along with the debt collection companies who hire them and keep hiring them even after they receive complaints of false service.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "343", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I am not a lawyer,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "but I have noticed that credit card agreements often contain statements advising consumers that if suit is brought, it will occur in a specified jurisdiction or \"as provided for by law.\"", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "At the point where collectors start suing consumers is where many consumers say enough and hire a bankruptcy attorney.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "The only winner in that situation is the bankruptcy attorney.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "536", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Ummm you want to know a annoying way to find out I was in collections... how about 12 voicemails saying they are bill collectors.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "Finding time to call you is not easy.", "reasons": ["2_3", "4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "Many of you work from 9 to 6.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "Thats when im at work.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "Some of you are different timezones.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "fact", "text": "Why cant I text or email you and haveyou text or email me back\"", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "So stone age!", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "913", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I too am a family member of a consumer who claims to have paid his debt of 12 - 15 years ago, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "but my husband and I receive two or three calls a day asking for him to call various agencies about a \"matter\" with a case #.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "In one instance they said they would be at the door in one hour.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "This family member has not lived here for about 16 years.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "policy", "text": "They should not be allowed to call anyone other than the debtor who nowadays can be found on the internet!!!", "reasons": ["0"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "238", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I still vividly remember receiving automated calls every Saturday morning in college insisting that I settle a debt under someone else's name.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "It was a case of mistaken identity, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "and eventually I sorted it out by tracking down the collection agency and calling them during business hours.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "This was a tremendous inconvenience, however.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "I strongly support limitations on robocalls, on total call volumes, and ask that you consider creating a complaint process for harassing or mistargeted calls.", "reasons": ["0_3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "policy", "text": "Collection agencies should face financial sanctions for misbehavior, payable to the target of their abuse.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "577", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "Being in a court of law and talking to a debt collector on the phone that requires proof that the debt in question is not a valid debt, are two different things.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "If your intent is to sue, then sue.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "But requiring proof from anyone you call up and demand that they prove to you (and not a judge) that the debt is not theirs is extortion.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "555", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "see robocalling, picking up just lets them know this is the prime time to make future calls since you're home at this time.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "Account keeps changing hands, repeat.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "\"It takes time for us to update our do not call lists...\"", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1036", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "What I mean is I have had my credit report cleared three times they were never on either of them.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "And when i think I have cleared all of my crediters they get a judgement and freeze my account.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1389", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "This is the problem.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "What account would stay open for 20 years after being delinquent.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "It seems to me this is just a way to prolong as long as possible the ability to harass people for very old debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "policy", "text": "There needs to be time limits.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "This type of thing, re-filing debt, selling the same debt to someone else, and then adding it back AGAIN to the credit report is just an excuse to harass the heck out of people and do it legally.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "These are not good business practices.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "This is harassment.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "policy", "text": "Once a debt is placed on a credit report -- or even sooner -- once the debt letter is sent, time should start running and this agency needs to set time limits that are reasonable.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "Creditors have a right to try to collect true, accurate debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "But what happens is the debt is wildly inflated, then it runs the gamut of various collection agencies until nobody even remembers its genesis.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "value", "text": "This is all to harass.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "506", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "Let's start by assuming the creditor provided something for which a consumer agreed to pay.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "Creditors should be entitled to get a phone number and address at which the creditor can reach the consumer and to get updates as long as a debt is outstanding.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "If a consumer chooses to use only a cell phone, the creditor and collector should be able to contact him at that number.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1248", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "Texts: No, text messaging and cell phones should be prohibited ", "reasons": ["1", "2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "as there is not a viable means for the consumer to record the text and bring it into court as documentation if needed.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "All the issues raised about collectors calling the wrong individual or family members would be 100x worse with texting.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "600", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I am on a Senior plan for my mobile phone ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "and I get charged for each text that comes in or goes out.", "reasons": ["0"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "I am able to make/receive texts, but have to pay for each one ...", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "so it is not fair to make me pay extra on top of what I already owe.", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "I am against using cell phones for business advertisements or debt collecting texts or calls.", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1086", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "fact", "text": "The Michigan program for handling NSF checks is outlined in Michigan statute (MCL 600.2952).", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "The statute provides the exact language to be used in the demand notice to the debtor but does not include the FDCPA Miranda language- which we add to the notice.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "We also send a copy of the dishonored check with the notice.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "The statute allows the debtor to pay the value of the check plus $25 is paid within 30 days of the notice, or $35 if paid thereafter.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "IF the creditor brings suit (after the first 30 days) they can sue for the value of the check, PLUS damages of 2 times the amount of the dishonored check PLUS $250 in costs.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "fact", "text": "This may even be used in small claims court.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "It seems that the idea is to penalize those who pass bad checks such that merchants will be willing to accept checks from customers.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "802", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I believe that most Defendants are properly served.", "reasons": ["1_2", "4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "I review about 200-300 civil cases a month", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "and very rarely is service done improperly.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "This does vary a bit from state to state", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "but in my experience the majority of defendants have been properly served.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1308", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "One such collection company used the actual phone number of a District Civil Court office in a neighboring county in their phone message for my wife to collect on a debt many years old.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "policy", "text": "This practice is deplorable and should have sever penalties towards any collection company/employee that uses this type of collection action.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1129", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I think it would.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "I work for an attorney at a debt collection law firm", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "and I think this would make things a lot easier and simpler.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1292", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Collectors constantly abuse laws concerning phone contacts, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "and there is no enforcement for violators.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "policy", "text": "Collectors should be limited by law to contacts by mail.", "reasons": ["0_1", "3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "These people are bottom-feeders who ignore the law.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "policy", "text": "Cut them off from phone contacts altogether.", "reasons": ["3", "5"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "They have proven again and again over decades that they are scofflaws.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "policy", "text": "No phone contacts.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "546", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "All i meant was that I know a lot of automated dialers. given the nature of my work.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "They don't magically redial.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "fact", "text": "The are forced to by the company.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "988", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "You are a liar!", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have been harassed for over 5 years by companies looking for someone I have never heard of ", "reasons": ["2"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "because this person put a random string of our area code, local exchange and 4 numbers together (that turned out to be my number) on a loan that he then defaulted on.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have told them to stop calling, they have a wrong number, and guess what\"", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "testimony", "text": "5 Years later, they are still calling!", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "884", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have been getting calls for a Hispanic gentleman with the same phone number as me in a different area code for years.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "testimony", "text": "Every time I tell them that I have no clue who he is and that I would like them to stop calling my number they assure me that they will get it fixed ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "but then I hear from them again a few weeks later.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "499", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "A simple request for a call back is the best.", "reasons": ["1", "2_3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "\"Foti\" messages serve no one.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "It's clear to everyone that the call is from a collector ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "and 3rd parties are unnecessarily inconvenienced.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "685", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I am sorry to hear about this situation.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "This kind of abusive behavior is upsetting to hear as a consumer.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "They don't need to \"speak\" with anyone.", "reasons": ["3"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "fact", "text": "You/your daughter are perfectly within your legal rights to ask the phone calls to stop and to communicate by other means.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "fact", "text": "And the collectors who are refusing to honor this request is in violation.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "policy", "text": "Moreover, they should not be contacting you", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "policy", "text": "nor they should be contacting you/your daughter 10 times a day.", "reasons": ["7"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "This is clearly excessive and abusive.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "value", "text": "I would like to also mention, that although they do have a point about the federal loans can usually be placed into deferment,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "fact", "text": "debt collectors are not fiduciaries", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "value", "text": "and are not acting with nor are capable of providing financial advice that is in the best interest of the consumer/debtor.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "value", "text": "The collectors will say anything and do anything just to get paid.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 12, "type": "policy", "text": "They should not be allowed to offer advice on what bills to pay and how to pay them.", "reasons": ["11", "13"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 13, "type": "value", "text": "This sort of \"advice\" can be detrimental to consumers/debtors.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 14, "type": "policy", "text": "Perhaps the CFPB should allow collectors to offer referrals on financial advice,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 15, "type": "policy", "text": "but they should not allow collectors to outright give financial advice.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1084", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "policy", "text": "These so called free-to-end-user alternatives (if allowed to be used) also need to be regulated.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "There are huge privacy concerns at stake here.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "My friend started texting me on a free texting app, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "testimony", "text": "and then all of a sudden I was begging to be bombarded by SPAM text and SPAM phone calls.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "I can't be certain that the Free Text App that my friend was using was selling my phone number to other people, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "but it was a massive coincidence.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "Why else are these text apps free?", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "value", "text": "How do they make their money (besides a few embedded ads)?", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "fact", "text": "Of course these people are selling phone numbers.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "My privacy is not for sell.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "value", "text": "Nor is my phone number.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "policy", "text": "The CFPB needs to really think about these so called free-to-end user alternatives and what sort of privacy practices these companies are engaging in, if any.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "1109", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "There are still too often abuses by debt collectors in regard to time-barred debts.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "Zombie debt collectors who use partial payments, acknowledgement of the debt in writing, or other tactics are effectively hard-wiring around the laws having to do with the statute of limitations.", "reasons": null, "evidence": ["2"]}, {"id": 2, "type": "testimony", "text": "I have witnessed situations where consumers were effectively tricked into setting up a series of payments on a long time-barred debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "Collectors continue to take advantage of consumers for whom ESL and also those who are unsophisticated and possibly naive.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "627", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "I think limitation is good as not to harass.", "reasons": ["3", "8_9"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "fact", "text": "I think it has been generally defined as 3-4 days per day, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "though I think that is still excessive, ", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "and any collector who follows that is clearly trying to harass.", "reasons": ["4"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "value", "text": "Who else would someone call 3-4 times in a day?", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "policy", "text": "But, with the example of 1 call per day, I would think that there would also need to be another limitation such as 1 call per day or no more than 4 calls in a week.", "reasons": ["6"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "Otherwise, a collector could call 1 time a day, 7 times a week, 30 times in a month, etc.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 7, "type": "testimony", "text": "And personally, in my personal phone calls and in my business phone calls, it can take me more than a day or two to return a message.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 8, "type": "testimony", "text": "Customarily, in personal phone calls and business phone calls, if a message is left, the caller will leave a message and wait a couple of days before calling back if the person has yet to return the phone call.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 9, "type": "value", "text": "This is the way normal phone etiquette works--both in personal phone calls and in business calls.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 10, "type": "value", "text": "So, why should debt collections be different,", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 11, "type": "value", "text": "why should they break the norms.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
{"id": "436", "propositions": [{"id": 0, "type": "value", "text": "Current debt substantiation requirements all suffer from the same significant shortcoming in that they fail to address the often symbiotic relationship between first-line creditors, collectors, reporting agencies, consumer data clearinghouses, buyers of bad debt, and others industry players.", "reasons": ["1"], "evidence": null}, {"id": 1, "type": "value", "text": "Each has a vested profit motive in the \"validation\" of debt.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 2, "type": "value", "text": "Without appropriate disincentive--i.e., enforcement of rules and stiff penalties for non-compliance--corners are cut and quid pro quo-type behaviors begin to surface.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 3, "type": "value", "text": "Consumers hold few cards and have to play against a stacked deck.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 4, "type": "policy", "text": "The validation process should involve more than merely inquiring with the creditor about the validity of the debt or the identity of the debtor, and failure to observe all the necessary steps--in the sunshine, no less--should have severe consequences.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 5, "type": "value", "text": "The best deterrent would be putting the power back in the hands of the (truly-wronged) consumer through the inclusion of \"private attorney general\" style enforcement mechanism.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}, {"id": 6, "type": "value", "text": "Awarding attorneys' fees and damages, with the ability to elect either actual or meaningful statutory damages (similar to the scheme introduced by Congress into the copyright statutes), would create serious disincentives for anyone involved in unscrupulous validation practices.", "reasons": null, "evidence": null}]}
